title: potato soup
directions: Put water in a large pot and bring to boiling.
Put in potatoes and cook until tender.
Put bacon in skillet and cook until crisp; remove and cook onions in bacon grease.
When potatoes are done, put in onions, salt, pepper, bacon and milk. Bring to a boil and add corn; boil a few minutes, stirring often after adding corn.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make and bake cake according to directions.
While cooking, mix pineapple and pudding.
Set aside in refrigerator.
When cake is cool, add Cool Whip to pudding mixture.
Spread on cake.

title: red pepper sauce
directions: Combine red pepper, butter and garlic in a 4-cup glass measure.

title: kielbasa bean pot
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole or bean pot. Bake uncovered for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the melted margarine, flour, sugar and chopped nuts; press into bottom of large baking dish (12 x 15-inch) and bake 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool completely.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Grease an 11 x 7-inch pan; set aside. Put chips and peanut butter into saucepan; melt over low heat just until warm.
Add marshmallows and nuts. Pour into greased pan and spread evenly. Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger with onions and garlic until browned.
Add mushroom soup and sherry to hamburger mixture in crock-pot.
Stir to blend.
Cover and simmer on low for 5 to 6 hours.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Check and correct seasonings.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream the margarine, confectioners sugar and peanut butter. Add vanilla and mix.
Form small balls.
Chill.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, mix together sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa. Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter. Stir until melted.
Add vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: piccadilly dip
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Mix all ingredients and heat in microwave until cheese is completely melted or prepare in crock-pot on high for 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Stir occasionally.
Keep hot in crock-pot or chafing dish.
Serve with corn chips.

title: italian bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: wild rice sausage stuffing
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add box of Rice-A-Roni wild rice and flavor packet.
Let simmer 20 minutes.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Contains no baking powder, no soda and no shortening!

title: crab and mushroom quiche
directions: Combine eggs, half and half, onion, salt and cayenne pepper; blend until smooth, then set aside.
Drain crabmeat on towels until it is very dry.
Sprinkle crabmeat, mushrooms and cheese over bottom of pie shell.
Pour in egg mixture; top with chopped parsley.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 more minutes, or until knife inserted in the quiche comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot vichyssoise
directions: Melt margarine; add onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute until soft.
Add salt, tomatoes with juice, potatoes, thyme, bay leaf and parsley; simmer 10 minutes.
Add fish and simmer 15 minutes.

title: holiday poke cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare, bake and cool cake mix as directed on package for 2 (9-inch) round cake layers.
Place cake layers, top side up, in 2 clean 9-inch round cake pans.
Pierce cake with large fork at 1/2 inch intervals.
Stir 1 cup of boiling water into each flavor of gelatin in separate bowls 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Carefully pour red gelatin over 1 layer and lime over the second layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Dip 1 cake pan in warm water 10 seconds, unmold onto serving plate.
Frost.
Unmold second layer, carefully place on first layer.
Frost top and sides.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Heat together the broth and mushrooms, including the juice. Blend the flour, garlic salt, pepper and milk. Stir into the broth and cook until thickened. Remove from the heat and stir in the grated cheese. Mix together the cut up chicken, cooked rice and peas. Pour into a buttered casserole dish. Add the broth mixture. Top with French onions. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave rice pilaf
directions: Combine butter, onion and celery in 1 1/2-quart glass dish. Cover and bake on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Add broth.
Cook on High until boils (3 to 5 minutes).
Add rice.
Stir and cook 15 to 18 minutes on Simmer 50% power.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Four ounces chopped mushrooms can be added when you add the rice.

title: country fried potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Fry in hot Crisco over low heat in 10-inch pan.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. When underside of potatoes have browned, turn and fry slowly on other side.
Leave skillet uncovered.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together the soups, lemon juice and mayonnaise. Layer the rice, broccoli, chicken and soup mixture.
Top with cheese, bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Put tomatoes in a blender just on low to lightly chop up.
Pour in skillet with beef.
Add tomato sauce and tomato soup (no water).
Add garlic, oregano and brown sugar.
Simmer on low for about 30 minutes.
In a large pot, boil mostaccioli until tender (do not overcook or it gets mushy). Drain.

title: spanish delight
directions: Brown onions and ground meat, then add tomatoes and corn and let cook on top of stove until tomatoes have cooked down.
Boil macaroni in salted water.
Put a layer of macaroni in casserole and a layer of cheese.
Alternate ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: apple butter
directions: In a large, heavy pot, place apples.
Cover with cider vinegar and cook until soft.
Add sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, allspice, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Cover tightly.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Uncover and cook quickly, until thick and smooth.
Stir with wooden spoon so mixture won't stick and burn.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, then let cool completely.
Mix jello and water, then let cool.
Add strawberries to the jello mixture.

title: southwestern bean soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheeses and corn chips. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup Jack cheese and Cheddar until melted.
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with remaining cheese and corn chips.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Cream together cream, sugar and milk.
Beat until fluffy. Pour into pie shell.
Top with strawberries that have been sliced, sweetened and drained.
Freeze at least 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool, then slice into 4 layers.
Mix sour cream, pineapple and sugar.
Put this between layers.
Save 1 cup and mix with Cool Whip for icing.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let stand, covered with ice, for at least 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture.
Bring to a boil, pack into hot jars, cover and seal.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well by hand. Pack firmly in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream white and brown sugars.
Cut shortening in.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add flour, oatmeal, baking soda and salt. Stir in orange slice pieces.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ham and dill dip
directions: Mix together and put into hollowed out sourdough or pumpernickel bread.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter in well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan (or Pyrex).
Sprinkle half of cheese on top.
Spread remaining batter over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes until cheese begins to brown and edges crust.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each. Next add flour and milk (starting with flour and ending with flour).
Then add vanilla and cocoa.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into 4 greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake layers approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Beat potatoes, sugar, eggs, sweet milk until no lumps in potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill dough, roll out and cut.
Fry on each side to desired browness in hot grease.
Test with fork - if it comes out clean, they're done.

title: walnut pie
directions: Beat egg whites, adding sugar slowly.
Crumble walnuts and crackers into egg white mixture.
Cut butter into small squares and spread over bottom of pie pan (leave butter chunky, do not melt).
Pour mixture into pie pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Place seeds on jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with oil and salt. Roast in oven at 250° until crisp. Stir often.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook with just enough water to cover potatoes, celery and onions.
When done, add a pint of half and half to the liquid. Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch or flour.
Bring to a boil; enjoy good eating.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt cheese, chocolate chips and oleo together in microwave or double boiler. Add powdered sugar and nuts.
Put into 9-inch square dish and refrigerate. When chilled, cut into squares.

title: summer squash soup
directions: Do not peel squash.
Slice squash thin.
Add celery leaves and onion.
Add bouillon cubes and cook until thickened.
Add more water, if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
If thicker soup desired, put all in blender until smooth.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in oil, water, pumpkin, eggs, nuts and raisins.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs together.
Add milk and flavor. Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for an hour (the center will be a little shaky).

title: one egg banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with a fork in a bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients until combined.
Pour batter into a buttered loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: hot green tomato pickles
directions: Pack quart jars with tomatoes, onions and hot peppers.
Mix water to vinegar and sugar per quart.
Heat liquids to boiling and pour in jars and seal.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake the cookie dough in a glass pie plate until done (about 14 minutes).
When it is cool, spread the cream cheese and sugar mixture on top.
Pat the fruit dry; place on top.
If it is for the next day, wait to add the fruit.
Some common fruits are: strawberries, grapes, oranges, peaches, kiwi or bananas dipped in lemon juice to stop browning.

title: hushpuppies
directions: Mix ingredients well. Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease or oil used for frying. Turn to brown, if necessary.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Moist chocolate cake, is better the day after.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in casserole.
Top with onion and pepper. Mix other ingredients and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix jello according to directions on box.
In a large glass bowl, layer 1/2 of each ingredient as listed, then continue the same with the other half.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Let stand.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder, melted shortening, sugar and egg together. Spread over apples.
(This mixture will be quite thick but once in the oven, it will spread out.) Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: black bean dip
directions: Drain beans.
Mash beans and add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/4 cup of cheese.
Pour into a 1-quart baking dish. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
After 10 minutes, pour on remaining cheese and bake until melted.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix flour into sugar.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Stir well.
Add milk, then vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mary's hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add eggs, nuts, coconut and pineapple.
Combine well, but do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a large skillet with margarine.
Pork chops should be cooked all the way through prior to the next step. Add 2 1/2 cups water to skillet and simmer pork chops for 15 to 20 minutes on medium-high heat.
Add flour to 1 cup warm water; mix well.
Salt and pepper simmering pork chops.
Add flour to the skillet, stirring constantly.
Add more water if gravy is too thick.

title: poor man pecan pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Heat until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until firm.

title: pecan pie(will make 2 pies)
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into 2 uncooked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, reduce heat.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes. Add icing and mix with cake batter. Spray a tube pan with nonstick spray. Place pecans in the bottom of the tube pan and pour batter on top of the nuts. Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fried ham and pineapple
directions: Put butter
into

frying pan and melt.	Brown pineapple slices in	melted butter.	Put pineapple aside after browning. Add a little Crisco and fry ham.	Make Syrup and pour over ham which has been topped with pineapple slices.

title: sweet potato bars
directions: With a fork, mix cake mix (but not the 1/2 c. reserved), 1 egg, 1/3 c. oil and the 1/2 c. pecans.
Spread in a 9x13-inch baking dish.
In another bowl mix the mashed potatoes, Eagle brand milk, 2 eggs, brown sugar and the 1/2 c. cake mix and vanilla. Pour over cake mixture.
Then mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and the box of powdered sugar and pour over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with milk and fruit, if desired.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese by hand or food processor. Spread in 9 x 13 dish. Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper and set aside.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Add onion; simmer until golden yellow. Add ground beef.
Stir with fork while onion browns lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a bean pot or 2-quart casserole. Bake in hot 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Heat the egg whites and sugar in double boiler to 150°. Transfer to a very large bowl and beat to a meringue.
Cream the shortening and powdered sugar in largest mixing bowl.
Add half of the meringue.
Mix.
Now add rest of meringue and beat a few minutes.
Flavor and color to suit.
I flavor with 1 teaspoon vanilla and use on a white cake.
Tastes just like a wedding cake.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel, wash and slice potatoes.
Spread layer of potatoes in bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour; then dot with butter.
Repeat layers until 3/4 full, then pour milk over layers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: garbanzo-bean dip(hummus-arabic)
directions: Place beans in blender or food processor.
Process well.
Add sesame seed paste, garlic, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Shape mixture into a mound on a flat plate.
Press your finger in center of mound to make an indentation.
Fill indentation with oil.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: unleavened or communion bread
directions: Mix flour and shortening with a fork.
Add ice water slowly and only a little at a time.
Mix until all flour is moistened and dough forms a ball.
Divide dough into thirds.
Roll out on a lightly floured board.
Cut in 4-inch circles.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick all over with a fork.
Mark each circle across the back of a knife so it can be broken in half when placed on a plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until thoroughly dry, but not very brown.
Cool on rack before storing.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind and drain.
Add 1 cup sugar to 1 cup vinegar until all the relish is covered.
Boil sugar and vinegar.
Pour relish in and boil 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and keep the juices.
Beat one egg and 1 tablespoon flour.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and mix well.
Add pineapple and orange juices to egg mixture and cook over medium heat until it cooks slightly.
Pour over fruit while still hot.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Spray a spring-form pan, 9 x 3-inches, with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs on bottom of pan.
Beat Thick Yogurt and cheese in medium bowl on medium speed until smooth.
Add sugar, milk, flour, vanilla and egg whites.
Beat on medium speed about 2 minutes or until smooth.

title: snowball salad
directions: Mix nondairy whipped topping, sour cream, sugar and lemon juice.
Add bananas, pecans, pineapple and cherries.
Pour into large dish.
Chill overnight or freeze.
Better if frozen.

title: low-fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, cream brown sugar, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat in egg whites.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients alternately with water. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no-egg chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Measure water, oil and vanilla in large jar (do not stir).
Add all at once to dry mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in vinegar; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Frost as desired or split in layers.
Spread cherry pie filling between layers, top with Cool Whip or real whipped cream.

title: southern style cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Turn into a hot, well-oiled pan.
Smooth oil over entire top of batter.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven until sides shrink from pan, approximately 25 minutes. Serve immediately.
Double this recipe for cornbread dressing.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dry chicken and place in pan.
Roll chicken in margarine; coat well.
Leave in pan. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper over chicken.
Pour rice around chicken.
Dice onion; sprinkle over chicken.
In bowl, dilute 2 cans of soup with 2 cans of water.
Mix well.
Pour slowly over chicken.
Makes sure all rice is covered.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook 1 hour or until tender.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Heat soup, milk and dash of pepper.
In buttered casserole dish, alternate layers of potatoes, onions, soup mixture and cheese.
Dot top with butter.
Cover.
Bake at between 350° and 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are cooked.
Uncover about the last 15 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add 2 cups water; simmer until meat is tender.
Add onion, celery and soy sauce; cook for 10 minutes. Rinse and add vegetables and bean sprouts.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Thicken with mixture of sorghum, cornstarch, ginger and 1/4 cup water.
Serve over rice.

title: potatoes - au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on (no salt).
Cool, peel and cube. In saucepan, melt butter; add flour and salt.
When this thickens, remove from heat.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Return to heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Place potatoes in casserole or cake pan; pour sauce over.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: butter mochi
directions: Melt butter and set aside to cool.
Mix all ingredients, adding coconut milk last.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with Crisco, margarine, etc.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. (Watch so it doesn't burn.)
Cool and cut.

title: oriental chicken rice salad
directions: Add enough water to chicken broth to make 2 1/2 cups liquid. Cook rice in liquid according to package directions.
Transfer to large bowl.
Combine oil, soy sauce, salt and if desired, sesame seed; mix well.
Stir into hot cooked rice.
Cover and chill. Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: lemon chiffon pudding
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour. Add lemon juice, beaten egg yolks and milk. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in custard cups set in a pan of warm water. Bake at 360° for 25 minutes.

title: more than cabbage
directions: In skillet, saute the onion and cabbage in water until soft. Add seasoning and simmer.
Serve warm.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in medium bowl.
Blend soup and milk in medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add cheese and heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add cheese mixture to noodle mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.

title: diane's grilled shrimp
directions: Marinate shrimp with tails in salad dressing at least one hour.
Turn or toss every 15 minutes.
Either put shrimp on skewers or on a grilling pan.
Cook on hot grill 10 minutes each side.

title: fill-er-up potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes (in round slices).
Dice onions.
In large bowl, mix soup, milk, onions and potatoes.
Make sure the potatoes are coated well.
Place into casserole dish.
Cook in oven or microwave oven until potatoes are tender.
Then put Cheddar cheese on top and continue cooking until cheese melts.

title: party punch
directions: Mix and serve. That's a tough one!

title: raspberry pretzel jello
directions: Step 1:
Dissolve jello in boiling water and add raspberries; stir until thawed.
Chill in refrigerator until syrupy (about 1 hour).

title: lincoln log
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce and celery seed. Beat until fluffy. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Shape into a 7 x 1 1/2-inch log. Roll in walnuts. Insert rosemary or parsley sprigs for the branches. Serve with crackers. Yield: 2 cups.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Slice and cut muffins into quarters (8 pieces from each muffin).
Melt butter. Add cheese and crabmeat.
Spread on muffins.
Broil 4 to 6 minutes.

title: baked spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Cut ribs into 2 to 3 rib pieces.
Put in a large roasting pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast in a 450° oven for about 1/2 hour, turning ribs occasionally until brown.
Reduce heat to 350°. Cook 1 hour longer, not covered.
Remove from oven and drain off fat.
Add undrained sauerkraut, apples, caraway seed, pepper and onion to the ribs. Cover.
Continue roasting at 350° until ribs are tender and meat will slip easily from the bones, about 1 hour. Add water, if necessary, during last of cooking.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook together in casserole with cover for 2 3/4 hours.
Add 1 cup frozen peas and cook 15 minutes more. Mix 3 tablespoons of flour in water (about 3/4 cup).
Add slowly to thicken stew.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese in pimento spread; add 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Mix thoroughly and add dried beef.

title: lou's very rich chocolate pie
directions: Mix and press into a 9-inch greased pan. Chill until firm.

title: deviled pork chops
directions: Brown the chops.
Combine all other ingredients with water. Mix well and pour over pork chops.
Cook slowly until chops are tender, about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese with fluffy.
Add powdered sugar gradually. Stir in melted chocolate and add vanilla.
Blend well.
Press into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.

title: red ring pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in water and lime for 24 hours.
Wash real good, then soak for 3 hours in cold water.
Drain it.
Put in pot with 1 cup cider vinegar, alum and red coloring.
Add enough water to cover; simmer for 2 hours.
Drain off and throw away.
Make syrup with 2 cups cider vinegar, 10 cups sugar, red hot cinnamon candy and 8 sticks of cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and pour over rings.
Let stand overnight, t hen drain syrup off into pot. Reheat syrup and pour back over rings; let set 24 hours.
Repeat again.
Then put in pot and let rings come to a boil.
Jar up in hot sterile jars.

title: "quicky" potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: maple syrup pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add maple syrup and beat again.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potpourri
directions: Crush the anise seed with the cloves, using a mortar and pestle.
Crack the nutmeg with a hammer.
Break the cinnamon into 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces.
Add the remaining ingredients, stirring gently, but well.
Place in a tightly sealed jar.

title: quick chicken rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine chicken broth, rice, spinach, pepper and chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat; simmer about 15 minutes.
When serving, garnish each bowl with 1 teaspoon cheese. Serves 4 (1 1/2 cups each).
Calories:
161; 3 gr. fat (for less fat, omit cheese or use fat free cheese).

title: super quick sticky buns
directions: In small bowl, combine margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup. Blend well.
Spread evenly in bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch round pan.
Remove dough from can and separate into 8 coils.
Do not unroll breadsticks!
In shallow dish, combine sugar and cinnamon. Dip both sides of each coil in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Arrange coils in pan.
Sprinkle with any remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 19 to 24 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: stained glass gelatin
directions: To make first layer, dissolve black cherry gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water; add 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour thin layer into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.
When it is firm, make the next layer by dissolving cherry gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/4 cup cold water and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Allow layer to firm.
Mix the third layer like the first with water, then the fourth with water and evaporated milk.
Alternate each layer and allow each layer to firmly chill before adding next layer.
Use a spoon to slow down pouring so each layer will be smooth.
And while one layer is sitting in the refrigerator, mix the next and let it cool so it will be ready to pour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Mix oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Line pizza pan or cookie sheet with dough and bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken and stuffing(serves 6)
directions: Mix chicken, peas, almonds, soup, milk and 1/3 cup stuffing mix.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix hot water and butter; spread over all.
Spread 2/3 cup stuffing mix over top.
Cover and bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: cherry-pineapple bread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Mash bananas and add baking soda.
Mix flour, pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Stir all ingredients together and pour into 4 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: firecracker casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and drain; add refried beans and cooked rice.
Add spices and simmer for 5 minutes.
Line 13x9 pan with 3-4 tortillas.
Pour meat mixture in pan.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Combine soup and tomatoes in bowl.
Pour over top of tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with sour cream on side.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°; reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
Mix remainder of cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Press this into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: chocolate cookie cheesecake
directions: Whirl 1/2 package of cookies, including filling, in food processor until they form fine crumbs. (Or crush in bag with a rolling pin.)
Mix in butter.
Scoop crumbs into 9-inch cheesecake pan with removable bottom and press evenly over bottom and about 1/2-inch up sides. Chill about 20 minutes until firm.

title: sweet crackers
directions: Use just enough water to hold ingredients together but not sticky.
Roll or pat out onto cookie sheet, pie crust thickness. Bake at 275° for 1 hour until it is golden brown.
Before baking, cut dough into 1-inch squares.

title: joe's special
directions: Saute onion slightly with oil and butter. Add ground beef. Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic salt over meat while browning, then add garlic and saute lightly. Add wine.
Add spinach, stirring frequently, until thawed out and cooked.
Blend cheese in well, then add mushrooms.
Mix in eggs a few minutes before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add chocolate, vanilla, flour and nuts.

title: swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle a little water over steak.
Press flour into steak. Brown steak; remove from frypan and place in oven pan.
Set aside. In frypan, pour water and loosen browned juice and pour over meat with other ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours at 300° or on low stove top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour, onion, salt and pepper. Cook. Stir constantly until bubbly; remove from heat. Stir in broth and milk; heat to boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Stir in chicken, peas and carrots. Pour into pastry-lined pan. Place top pastry over chicken mix. Bake 35 minutes at 425°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni noodles according to directions on box; rinse and drain.
Combine milk and flour in saucepan on medium heat until slightly thickened.
Reduce heat to simmer and add the butter and 1/2 block Velveeta cheese until melted.
Simmer and stir until creamy (should not be extremely thick).

Cube a block each of the Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack/Colby and 1/2 block Velveeta cheese. Add cubed cheese and pour cheese sauce over macaroni (if not a little soupy, you will need to add extra milk).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour, depending on depth of pan you use.

title: bethel pickles
directions: Drain and rinse pickles with cold water.
Slice thin. Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Pour this mixture over the sliced dills and let set 4 to 6 hours.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off all fat.
In large saucepot, mix Ragu, ground beef, onions, mushrooms and seasonings.
Bring to boil and let simmer for 45 minutes to an hour.
Cook noodles to desired doneness.
In a glass oblong casserole dish, layer ingredients in the following order:
noodles, sauce, Parmesan cheese, Ricotta and Mozzarella.
Finish with a layer of noodles topped with sauce.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: chocolate nut drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° preheated oven.

title: breakfast strada
directions: 1. Brown and drain meat. 2. In 13 x 9 pan place uncooked crescent rolls flat down.
Press seams together. 3. Spread meat on top of rolls.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over top half of meat. 4. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until egg is done.
Great for any meal.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil, sour cream and eggs.
Mix well and pour half of batter into greased tube pan.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Place 1/4 mixture into tube or Bundt pan.
Add 2 cans of biscuits, torn into fourths, on top of melted mixture.
Add another 2/4 of melted mixture, then 1 can of torn biscuits.
Then add the last 1/4 of mixture and last can of torn biscuits.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Turn upside down onto plate immediately after baking.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and grease and flour a bread loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Great the next day for sandwiches.

title: kathy's squash
directions: Mix together, then sprinkle a couple of tablespoons of brown sugar on top.
Cover while cooking.
Bake in oven at 350° for about an hour.
Stir once or twice while cooking.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: low country boil
directions: *Shrimp or crab must be cleaned and ready to cook.

title: corn bread
directions: Bake at 425° for 25 minutes in a 9-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: *Use just enough milk to soften the crackers.

title: red raspberry pie
directions: Cook until clear, then cool until lukewarm.
Fill baked shell with berries.
Pour the glaze mixture over berries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Add pineapple and stir. Pour into baking dish and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Top with marshmallows and bake until brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Stir sugar, milk, corn syrup and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly (candy thermometer 234°) or to soft ball stage.

title: jackson burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Knead until all ingredients are blended.
Shape into 4 patties.
Place patties over hot coals and grill until cooked to your desire.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and freeze in a freezer tray.

title: tropical carrot cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Prepare carrots, pineapple and walnuts.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs lightly.
Beat in sugar. Stir in oil, and dry ingredients.
Add carrots and pineapple. Mix well.
Stir in walnuts and coconut.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until sides shrink slightly and top springs back on touching.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients together.
Heat to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Let set overnight.

title: martha's waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat milk, egg yolks and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour into hot waffle iron. Makes three 9-inch waffles.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash and bake ungreased potatoes in a 450°
oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove and cut each potato lengthwise and scoop out insides with a spoon.
Make sure to leave a wall of skin and potato to leave a substantial hollow bowl.

title: chocolate icing
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, oil, milk and oleo; bring to a hard boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Beat 3 to 5 minutes or until ready to spread on cake.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in skillet until crumbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook until heated through, stirring frequently.

title: steak and brown rice dinner
directions: Heat pressure cooker.
Add oil and brown meat.
Remove meat from pressure cooker; add remaining ingredients and stir well. Place meat in pressure cooker.
Clove cover and place pressure regulator on vent pipe.
Cook 15 minutes.
Let pressure drop of its own accord; remove meat.
Fluff rice mixture with a fork while steaming.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: captain's stew
directions: Brown beef in butter or margarine with salt, onion and celery salt.
Add beef broth, diced carrots with juice and green beans. Then add diced potatoes and soups.
Add 1/2 can water.
Simmer until potatoes are cooked (approximately 45 minutes).
Serve with corn bread or biscuits.

title: great guacamole
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender or food processor until smooth.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8.
Contains per serving: 0 grams fat and 54 calories.

title: tabbouleh(lebanese; international)
directions: Place the burghul in a bowl or pan and pour in enough cold water to cover it completely. Let it soak for about 10 minutes, then drain in a sieve or colander lined with a double thickness of dampened cheesecloth. Wrap the burghul in the cheesecloth and squeeze it vigorously until dry. Drop the burghul into a deep bowl; add the tomatoes, parsley, onions, lemon juice and salt and toss gently but thoroughly together with a fork.

title: peach chiffon salad
directions: Drain peaches, add enough water to make 1 cup.
Heat juice to boiling and pour Jell-O in.
Chill until syrupy.
Add cut up peaches, cheese and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in bowl. Chill until firm.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread graham crackers over cookie sheet.
Boil butter and sugar for 2 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and pour over graham crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan with a greased spatula and put on greased wax paper.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add chocolate; stir until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in Equal and vanilla.
Combine chocolate mixture with cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1 inch squares.
Makes 64 squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together except Tater Tots and cheese. Then alternate Tater Tots and meat mixture in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until Tater Tots are done.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; blend beaten egg yolks.
Add buttermilk and melted butter.
Gradually blend buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients, fold in egg whites.
Pour into pie shells and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease or butter 9 to 10-inch spring-form pan.
Line the pan with graham cracker crumbs, very lightly, just enough to coat pan.
Mix first four ingredients until well blended.
Then add next three ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pan.
Bake one hour at 375° or until knife in center of cake comes out clean.
Turn oven off and let it stay in oven for 1 hour. (Leave door of oven open.)
Cool and refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours. Add pie filling to top of cake at anytime.
Comstock cherry, blueberry or pineapple can be used as topping.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pat in bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Mix in eggs and bananas. Sift dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and bake in greased, floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil mixture.
Pour over cooked beets.
Simmer 5 minutes. Mixture covers 6 pints beets.

title: bible cake
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients to a cream.
Add the next ingredient, one at a time.
Still beating, add the next 3 ingredients.
Mix the next 4 ingredients and add to the mixture. Finally, add the last ingredient.

title: easy homemade ice cream
directions: Add Eagle Brand and vanilla to ice cream freezer.
Fill with milk (1/2 to 1 gallon, depending on size of freezer).
Stir thoroughly.
Freeze.

title: macaroni hamburger meal
directions: Use directions on package to prepare Kraft macaroni and cheese dinner.
While macaroni is cooking, crumble hamburger in skillet and brown; season with salt and pepper as desired.

title: no bake church windows
directions: In double boiler, melt together chocolate chips and butter until blended.
Add chunky peanut butter and mix well.
In large bowl, mix together marshmallows, coconut and walnuts.
Add chocolate-peanut butter mixture and blend.
Put into a Pyrex dish and let cool, about 20 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Keep sealed and refrigerated.

title: ginger pear dessert
directions: Place pears cut-side up in baking dish.
Drizzle with orange juice.
Sprinkle with mixture of cookies, sugar, nuts and butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until pears are tender.
Serve warm with whipped cream topping, if desired.

title: best caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine and white syrup and boil for 5 minutes; take off heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Butter a large pan; bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer until thickened, about 5 minutes.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Saut meat, onions and spices; drain.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir cornstarch and bouillon into meat mixture.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes or cooked noodles.

title: fried bananas
directions: Prepare pancake mix.
Slice bananas.
Heat oil, hot.
Put bananas in batter and fry in oil until golden brown.
Remove and sprinkle with sugar.
Serve hot.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Cook pineapple juice in top of double boiler until hot.
Add sugar, salt, flour and eggs.
Cook until thick.
While cooking, cut pineapple chunks smaller and oranges.
When dressing is cool, pour over fruit.
Chill.
Add whipping cream, coconut, marshmallows and pecans.
Chill.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Pour milk into large mixing bowl and chill in freezer until crystals form around the edge.
Dissolve jello in boiling water. Pour over cream cheese and beat with mixer until smooth.
Add sugar, lemon juice and vanilla. Chill.

title: apple raisin walnut cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil in a mixing bowl until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Continue to beat.
Add apples, beating slightly.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add raisins and walnuts to flour mixture.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture.
Beat slightly.
Bake at 350° in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Check for doneness after 25 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Stir sugar, salt, margarine and potatoes together.
Pour hot milk over it.
When lukewarm, add yeast mixture, half of flour and beaten eggs.
Add rest of flour.
Let rise until doubled in size. Bake at 350°.
(Work like bread dough.)

title: papier-mache
directions: Mix water and flour in large bowl until smooth.
Should be the consistency of heavy cream.
Coat a mold (inflated balloon, or molded clay) with one layer of news paper strips dipped in water. Then dip strips in flour mixture and lay over first layer until mold is well coated.
Let stand until strips are dry and hard. Paint over strips, if desired.
Can paint faces, etc.

title: tomato cake(pancakes)
directions: Mix all ingredients and add milk until thin enough to drop in pan with spoon.
Fry.

title: heavenly dirt
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix pudding and milk. Combine cheese mixture and pudding with wire whisk.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Alternate layers with crushed Oreo cookies.
Save crumbs for topping.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Melt cheese and milk in double boiler. Add pimentos, sugar and beaten egg. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Take off stove. Add mayonnaise. Let cool.

title: beef stew
directions: Line greased casserole pan with beef chunks.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Mix celery soup with mushroom soup.
Pour over meat and potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Do not stir.

title: steamed vegetables
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in steaming rack.
Place rack over boiling water; cover and steam 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Transfer vegetables to serving dish; add butter, lemon juice, salt and pepper and toss gently.
Sprinkle with chives.

title: posh squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion; do not overcook.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients to eggs.
Drain squash and onion; add to mixture.
Add cheese.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock pot hamburger dish
directions: Place vegetables in crock pot and season with salt and pepper.
Put in hamburger and cover with soup and water.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.
Stir once or twice while cooking.

title: john wayne's cheese casserole
directions: Beat egg yolks with milk and flour and season with salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks.
Fold these into egg yolk mixture.
In a deep, well-buttered casserole, mix shredded cheese with chilies.
Pour egg mixture over chilies and ooze it through.
Place in a preheated oven and bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven and place on top of sliced tomatoes or canned tomatoes.
Return to oven and bake another 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large glass dish, spray with Pam.
Place frozen broccoli in dish.
Mix all the ingredients in bowl; pour over broccoli. Mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° until brown. Add potato chips before serving.

title: lasagna italiano
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
In an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, layer half of noodles, meat sauce, Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese; repeat layers. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: tropical fruit
directions: Cook pudding with juice drained from fruit.
Cool.
Add bananas just before serving (chill well).

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and water; mix well.
Bake in 2 layers in 9-inch pans at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef into 1/8-inch strips, lengthwise.
Butcher can do this.
Heat butter in a large frying pan and cook onions and garlic, stirring constantly, until golden. Add mushrooms and saute until golden. Remove onions, garlic and mushrooms to a small bowl.

title: chicken in marsala wine
directions: (I use an electric skillet.)
Melt oleo, garlic and rosemary. Dip chicken in flour, brown in mixture.
Pour wine over chicken and simmer 5 minutes.
Bake in uncovered casserole dish for 30 minutes.
(I make several batches ahead of time and freeze.
I prepare up to the point where they would go in the oven.
After they are thawed, then it can be finished in oven.)

title: carrots
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Add carrots, sugar, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Cover tight and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in casserole dish and cook in oven 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: party cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix together cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Spread on bread.
Add on top a thin slice of cucumber (leave skin and score with fork).
Sprinkle dill weed on top of cucumber.
(People who don't like cucumbers even like this!)

title: fruit medley
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple chunks.
Combine fruit cocktail and pineapple chunks with undrained mandarin orange segments.
Stir in dry vanilla pudding and breakfast drink.
Add apples and stir to make sure each chunk is covered with fruit sauce.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Grate cheese and pepperoni.
Mix flour, eggs and milk.
Add cheese and pepperoni.
Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in dry sauce mix, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Place mozzarella cheese slices on top.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Top mixture with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
This salad is good without the chips.

title: hot bean dip
directions: In medium saucepan, combine beans, taco mix, onions, sour cream and cheese.
Stir occasionally over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: carrot cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, combine shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla, lemon rind and buttermilk.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to liquid ingredients, along with rolled oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Stir just until moistened.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: peach butter
directions: Mix peaches, sugar and salt in large kettle.
Boil rapidly, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Lower heat as the butter starts to thicken.
Add spices and continue cooking until butter is very thick.
Pour into sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch at top. Seal.

title: chicken wingettes
directions: Mix crumbs with cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Dip wings in butter and roll in crumbs mixture.
Pour remaining butter over wings in pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add mushrooms and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Slowly stir in broth and cream; cook, stirring until thickened.
Add the cut-up pimiento and heat well.
Serve on toast or croissants. Serves 6.

title: crunchy walnuts
directions: Beat egg white until fluffy; add sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir often.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press 2/3 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 2 loaves frozen bread dough, cut in pieces, over top.
Let rise and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: whole wheat raisin bread
directions: Combine flours, honey, butter, yeast, 1 to 2 tablespoons cinnamon and salt.
Cook 1 cup cold water and milk until temperature reads 105° to 115°.
Pour into flour mixture.
Knead into dough.
Place dough on lightly floured surface.
Cover with a damp cloth.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Cut dough in half on lightly floured surface.
Roll each half to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Sprinkle each with 1 cup raisins and 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon. Starting at shorter end, roll up dough to form a loaf shape.
Seal ends; fold sealed ends under.
Place seam side down in greased loaf pans.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pheasant casserole
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms and pheasant; add water chestnuts. Cook rice according to package directions.
Make a white sauce with the flour, butter, milk, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Toss pheasant-mushroom mixture and rice together.
Pour sauce over and toss again.

title: barbecued salmon steaks with avocado butter
directions: Salmon:
Place oil, 3 tablespoons lemon juice, barbecue spice, basil, marjoram, salt and pepper in a jar and shake well.
Arrange salmon in a casserole in a single layer.
Top with sauce and cover.
Refrigerate about 4 to 6 hours, turning occasionally. Reserve half of the sauce from salmon and broil steaks 2 inches from heat for about 4 minutes.
Turn and spoon on reserved sauce. Broil about 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve steaks topped with avocado butter.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
(Squeeze spinach if necessary.) Layer artichokes at bottom of casserole.
Layer spinach on top of artichokes.
In a separate bowl, soften cream cheese and butter. Add milk and pepper and mix until smooth.
Pour over spinach. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's peanut brittle
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients.
Add peanuts.
Cook and stir until nuts are light brown.
Take off fire.
Add oleo, soda and vanilla.
Spread out on well-greased cookie sheet.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Pat graham cracker crumbs and oleo in pan, 8 x 10-inch and bake 10 minutes.
Keep some for top.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and milk and spread over crumbs when cool. Whip Dream Whip and spread 1/2 over cheese mixture.
Spread 2 cans cherry pie filling over Dream Whip.
Then spread the rest of Dream Whip over top of cherries.
Let set in refrigerator for hours before serving.
Sprinkle a few crumbs over top.

title: polynesian chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Add chicken and coat well.
Cover and chill overnight.
Turn pieces.
Heat oven to 350°. Line large baking sheet with foil.
Arrange wings on sheet.
Bake approximately 1 hour, turning after 30 minutes.
May be served hot or cold.

title: apple praline pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, oleo and pecans.
Place half of this mixture on the bottom of 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Mix white sugar, lemon juice, apples and cinnamon.
Pour over mixture in pie shell.
Place other half of first mixture on top of apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry angel puffs
directions: Carefully slice cookies in half.
Whip together Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Drain most of juice from berries. Add to cream cheese mixture.
Put small amount of mixture on half of cookie and top with other half.
Cool before serving at least 1 hour.
May substitute 1 (8 ounce) can crushed pineapple or lemon pudding for berries.

title: creamy skillet cabbage
directions: In large pot or skillet, combine cabbage and vinegar.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 8 minutes or until cabbage is softened but still has some crunch.
Remove from heat.
Combine honey, mustard and yogurt.
Stir into warm cabbage just before serving.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 4 servings.
Contains 1 gram of fat and 73 calories per serving.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine asparagus, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can onions in medium bowl.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Cook water and margarine until boiling.
Add flour and salt and stir until mixture is in a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg is added. Drop by teaspoon on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° to 450° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut top half of Cream Puffs off.
Remove inside of Cream Puff that isn't done.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Fill Cream Puffs with pudding mixture.
Replace top of Cream Puffs.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Chill.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: easy pepper steak
directions: Place cooked rice in baking dish.
Heat soup, pour over rice and serve.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix soup mix, sour cream and softened cream cheese.
Add chopped olives and chill 1 hour.
Top sliced ham with mix.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Top again with mix.
Roll and place tightly in wax paper.
Place in coldest part of refrigerator until serving time.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Use desired proportions.
Layer into salad bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Peas will be thawed next day.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and 10x sugar.
Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased baking pan (12 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Lightly brown rice and onion whites. Add chicken broth.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Let simmer on low for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms, onion greens, salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 minutes.

title: zeppoli
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into very hot oil in deep fryer or large saucepan. Turn with a spoon until brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve warm.

title: spicy peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in 8-inch round glass cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg over sliced peaches, stir to coat.
Spread peaches over nuts.
Pour and spread 2 cups cake batter.
Cook on Medium heat in microwave for 4 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes, invert cake on plate.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 2 tablespoons juice. Mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky. Stir in flour. Mix baking powder with 2 tablespoons juice. Stir into other ingredients. Form into patties. Fry until brown.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Beat eggs in small mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Set aside.
Combine corn meal, salt and pepper.
Dip tomatoes in egg.
Coat with meal mixture.
Heat oil in large skillet or frying pan.
Fry tomato slices until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Empty pineapple into boiler with jello; bring to a boil.
Let cool slightly; add buttermilk and let cool for 30 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and beat.
Pour into mold.

title: frosty cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries through a food chopper, using fine blade. Quarter oranges and lemon; remove seeds.
Grind.
Add sugar and corn syrup.
Stir until sugar dissolves.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix vinegar, water, onion, salt pepper, and sugar in pot. Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes, cool.
Mix potatoes and vinegar mixture.
Add olive oil and Miracle Whip to taste.
Cover and place in freezer for 1 1/2 hours.
Before serving, add eggs on top.

title: ma-ma's red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour, alternating with buttermilk, beginning with flour and ending with flour.
Last, blend in food coloring.
Pour mixture into three 8-inch cake pans, or may use three 9-inch pans, which have been greased well and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baby wipes
directions: Mix liquids together.
Put towels in container.
Pour liquids over towels.
Cover and flip container over to coat evenly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
(Will be runny.)
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Can omit sprinkling with sugar and frost instead. Freezes well.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Cook pudding mix and milk until thickened.
Remove from heat; add pumpkin and spices.
Return to heat and cook until boiling. Remove from heat.
Let set until almost cool.
Mix cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar until smooth and add Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom crust.
Spread pudding over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with whipped topping and nuts if desired.

title: cashew nut casserole
directions: After cooking onions in oleo, add beef and stir.
Mix soup and Pet milk.
Heat and add to meat mixture.
Cook noodles.
Starting with noodles in baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, meat mixture and grated cheese.
Bake until bubbly hot.
Just before serving, sprinkle top with nuts and chow mein noodles and brown in oven.

title: caramel ice cream dessert
directions: Mix sugar, flour and oatmeal; add pecans and melted butter. Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Stir while hot, to make crumbs.
Line a 9 x 14-inch Pyrex pan with 1/2 of crumbs. Drizzle 1 bottle of sauce over this.
Fill with 1/2 gallon of ice cream.
Top with remainder of crumbs and then drizzle the second bottle of sauce over top of this.
Freeze overnight and serve.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix together whole wheat flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cut the margarine in with a pastry blender. Mix together egg, orange juice, yogurt and lemon peel and add to flour mixture. Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pans for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: sponge candy
directions: Butter a 9 x 11 or 10 inch square pan at least 2 inches deep. Combine sugar, corn syrup and vinegar.
Cook without stirring to 300 degrees on a candy thermometer or until small amount becomes brittle when dropped in cold water.
Remove candy from heat and quickly stir in baking soda.
Mix well, then turn into a lightly buttered pan.
The candy will spread by itself.
Do not spread with spoon.
When cool, break into pieces.
Coat with chocolate if desired.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package and bake at 350° on a large cookie sheet, 11 1/4 x 18 1/2-inch or 12 x 17 1/2-inch for 15 minutes.
Then cool.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together well.
When ready for a cup of hot beverage, take 2 or 4 teaspoons of the mix into cup and add hot water.
Store mixture in covered jar.

title: clam dip
directions: In medium saucepan, saute onion in melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
This can be fixed ahead and reheated before serving.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar, water and margarine in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, to thread stage.
Stir in peanuts and cook until golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and salt; blend quickly, but thoroughly.
Turn onto heavy greased baking sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake mix in long pan.
Cut in half; put half of cooked cake in punch bowl.
Add 1/2 pie filling on top of cake, then add 1 can pineapple, 1 can strawberry pie filling, 2 bananas, 1 box Cool Whip and 1/2 of nuts.
Repeat with the rest of the remaining ingredients; top with Cool Whip, nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: strom ball
directions: Thaw frozen loaf of bread and spread as thin as you want it. (Use oil on your hands and a rolling pin to help spread out loaf.) Put three packages of pepperoni and 1 package of cheese on rolled out dough and roll loaf up.
Pick seams
with a fork.
Beat one egg with 1 tablespoon water and spread on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: stove top smoked sausage
directions: Cut sausage in small pieces.
Cut bell pepper, celery and onion in medium pieces.
Precook sausage to a golden brown.
Add bell pepper, celery and onion; mix and stir for about 2 minutes. Cut heat off; cover with lid for 10 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter and combine with carrots.
Heat soup, salt, pepper and cheese until melted.
Pour over cooked carrots.
Pour all in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and top with croutons tossed with butter. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until heated through and topping is browned.

title: french coconut cake
directions: Beat 1 cup of butter until creamy.
Add 2 cups of sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, and beat until creamy.
Beat in egg, flour, baking powder and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Add alternately with milk and coconut juice.
Beat until smooth.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla. Bake in layers at 350° until cake tests done.

title: double good blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, and salt in saucepan. Add water and 2 cups blueberries. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and is thickened and clear. Mixture will be quite thick.

title: thousand island salad dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Then add pickle relish. Chill.

title: white chili
directions: Boil chicken breasts (season to taste with bouillon, salt and pepper) in enough water to have 6 cups stock. Measure 6 cups stock; set chicken breasts aside to cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put corn in greased baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over corn.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Place in dish of boiling water and bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: mint meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 375° for 15 minutes.
Beat egg whites until frothy and add sugar. Add a dash of salt and cream of tartar. Beat until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Tint with food coloring and fold in chips.
Drop by teaspoon as close together as possible onto greased sheets.
Place in oven and turn off immediately.
Do not open door for at least 5 hours.
May be left in overnight.

title: potato broccoli bake
directions: Steam potatoes in steamer for 5 minutes.
Blanch broccoli in steamer for 5 minutes.
Heat milk in suitable size kettle.
Make a roux by blending margarine and flour, mix together well.
Slowly add roux to hot milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add steamed potatoes, broccoli, salt, paprika, onions, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and dill weed; mix together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: peach and banana sherbet
directions: Pour milk into an ice cube tray; freeze.
Chill fruit well or freeze.
Shortly before serving, remove milk and peaches from freezer, if frozen.
Let stand about 5 minutes at room temperature.
Remove milk cubes from tray; cut them into small chunks if cubes are large.

title: succulent country ribs
directions: Brown ribs. Place in roasting pan.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to cream and mix, alternating milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes until cake is done.

title: gourmet zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, beat 3 eggs until frothy.
Beat in 2 cups sugar, 1 cup vegetable oil and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Beat mixture until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in 2 cups loosely packed, coarsely grated zucchini and 2 cups flour sifted with cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold in 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured loaf pans (8 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let loaves cool in pans for 10 minutes; then invert loaves on racks and allow to cool for 1 hour.

title: vermicelli hot dish
directions: Mix ground meats together with salt and pepper.
Form into small balls and brown.
Mix all other ingredients together (except mushrooms and cheese). Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add mushrooms with juice; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake another 30 minutes.
Makes a big roaster.

title: marshmallow cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth; add boiling water and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk. Add walnuts, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in two greased and floured 8 or 9 inch layer cake pans in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Turn out on racks to cool.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar again.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg white until soft peak will stand. Gradually add sugar and vanilla. Fold in pecans. Grease cookie sheet; spread 1-inch apart. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled vidalia onions
directions: Peel onions; cut slits in top of onion down to middle of onion.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of butter for each onion into slits. Season with salt and pepper.
Wrap in aluminum foil and cook on grill for approximately 30 minutes or until very tender.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute bacon until crisp.
Drain off all but one tablespoon of drippings. Add onion, green pepper and okra.
Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in rice, broth and seasonings. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Add tomatoes and fluff lightly.
Replace lid and let stand 12 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: poor man's crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into patties and coat with flour.
Fry in skillet with Crisco oil until brown, turning once.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil and 1/2 vinegar.
Mix at high speed in blender.
Add oil slowly, then vinegar slowly. Chill.

title: corny cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a skillet and spread brown sugar in skillet and pineapple on sugar and pecans.
Put a cherry in each pineapple. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar and pineapple juice and sifted flour.
Fold in whites of eggs that have been beaten until stiff.
Pour over pineapple and pecans in skillet.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine meats, 1/2 cup tomato sauce and all but Worcestershire sauce and parsley flakes.
Mix well.
Shape into a loaf.
Place on rack of lightly greased broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Combine other 1/2 cup tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and parsley flakes.
Stir well.
Pour over meat loaf and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick skillet potato pancakes
directions: In a small bowl, combine potato flakes and flour. Add remaining ingredients, except oil and applesauce and, using a fork, blend thoroughly. In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil. Drop batter into skillet by heaping tablespoons, forming 4 pancakes. Cook until bottoms of pancakes are browned. Turn pancakes and brown other side. Remove to serving plate and serve with applesauce.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix jello with fruit juices; add enough water to make 1 cup juice water. Chill until set but not firm. Mix together pretzels, sugar and margarine. Put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Do not grease pan. Cook in oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Cream together cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread on pretzel mix, then add fruit. Pour jello mix over fruit. Put back in refrigerator. Best if made day before.

title: bread
directions: Mix everything together.
Turn oven up really hot.
Cook for 7 days.
Make sure the oven is on 480°.
Put salt on top of it and pepper.
Then you eat it.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt and spice.
Add and stir until smooth the pumpkin, milk and beaten egg.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.

title: layered taco salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together refried beans, taco sauce and several dashes of bottled hot pepper sauce (if desired).
Spread refried bean mixture evenly on bottom and sides of Pyrex or Corning Ware dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over bean layer.
In a small bowl, combine the cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Beat with an electric mixer (medium speed). Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over the cheese.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir up first 5 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.

title: fresh blueberry cake pie(a pennsylvania dutch dessert)
directions: In a medium saucepan, over moderate heat, gently stir berries, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice until sugar is dissolved and mixture simmers.
Let cool to lukewarm.
In a medium bowl, cream butter with remaining sugar and vanilla.
Add egg.
Beat until fluffy. Add flour mixture (flour, baking powder and salt) alternating with milk.
Beat gently until smooth.
Fold in berry mixture just enough to marble.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ala mode.

title: finnish reiska
directions: Combine all dry ingredients. Work in fat. Add buttermilk to make a soft dough. Knead on floured board.
Pat out to desired size. Bake in greased 12-inch round pan at 400° for 30 minutes. Prick dough with work before baking.

title: white salad
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk in a double boiler pan.
Heat until melted.
Let mixture cool.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Pour into a 14 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: summer pies
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. Stir in coconut and pecans until brown and toasty. Pour into large bowl and let cool.

title: wonderful waffles
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and beat. Add egg yolks and melted butter; beat again.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites just before baking.

title: farmer's love letter
directions: My sweet potato, do you carrot all for me?
You are the apple of my eye.
With your radish hair and turnip nose.
My heart beets for you.
My love for you is as strong as onions.
If we cantaloupe, lettuce marry, and we will be a happy pear!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Use a double boiler. Mix salt and cornstarch together.
A smooth dough will result if salt and cornstarch are mixed very thoroughly.
Add cold water.
Stir the mixture constantly for several minutes as it quickly thickens into a solid mass, about the consistency of bread dough.
Place on aluminum foil or wax paper to cool.
Soak double boiler immediately for easier cleaning.
Knead like bread dough.
Place in airtight container.

title: best ever spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat with the onions and peppers.
Drain off grease; add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, mushrooms and olives.
Cook over medium heat; stirring often to heat thoroughly.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook until desired consistency.
Serve with your favorite pasta.

title: aunt viola's apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender in boiling unsalted water; drain thoroughly.
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and cook until onion is tender, but not brown.
Blend in condensed cream of chicken soup, milk and grated Parmesan cheese.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve sauce over hot cooked broccoli.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Mix in flour, paprika and salt. Shape 1 teaspoon dough around each olive.
Put on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Mix all ingredients and stuff grape leaves with about 1 heaping teaspoonful of filling, depending on size of leaves. Cover with 2 cups of boiling water and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill in freezer for 2 hours or until you can handle the dough.
Take 1 teaspoon of dough, roll into ball and roll in sugar, press onto cookie sheet with a glass dipped in sugar. Crisscross with fork.
Bake at
350° for about 12 minutes.

title: ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take meat off bones.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Saute onions and garlic in butter until tender.
Cut tortillas into fourths.
Dip in hot Crisco oil.
Remove fast! Blend Ro-Tel tomatoes and soups.
Add onion and garlic.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugars and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and pecans.
Shape into rolls, 2 inches thick. Chill until firm.
Slice and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: dirt
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients to the first mixture and set aside.
Grind cookies in food processor to small crumbs.
In a clean flowerpot, layer starting with creamed ingredients, then cookies, alternating, ending with crumbs on top.
Place a silk or plastic flower in the mixture.
Serve with a trowel.
You can also decorate with gummy worms.

title: karen's chili recipe
directions: All of the amounts of these ingredients can be adjusted to your personal taste.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Sift again into an ungreased oblong cake pan.
Make 3 depressions in sifted ingredients.
Pour cooking oil in one, vinegar into the second and vanilla into the third.
Pour water over all.
Mix with a fork until well mixed. Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp and rice recipe
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in oleo.
Add soups, parsley, shrimp, green onions and pimento.
Heat through.
Stir in rice and bread crumbs (1/4 cup).
Put into 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Can make ahead, freeze, bake and serve.

title: angel hash salad
directions: Cook together until thick, stirring constantly. Cool. Add whipped cream. Pour over fruit mixture.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Put shrimp in baking dish and pour melted margarine seasoned with Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and pepper over shrimp. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with French bread.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix pie filling, milk, cream cheese (broken into small pieces), pineapple and nuts.
Add whipped topping and stir until fluffy. Let sit one hour or overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: banana orange slush
directions: I substitute 1 package of sugar-free orange jello for the sugar.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add onion; cook a little.
Add rice, consomme and mushrooms.
Place in covered dish and bake about 30 minutes.

title: chicken simon and garfunkel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use wax paper, put chicken between the paper and roll over with rolling pin.
Brush with butter, season with salt and pepper.
Lay each chicken breast on a slice of cheese, roll up, fasten with toothpick.
Combine beaten egg with water.
Roll chicken in the flour, egg mixture and crumbs.
Evenly space in baking pan.
Combine melted butter with parsley, sage, rosemary and thyme.
Drizzle melted butter over chicken rolls. Bake for 30 minutes.
Pour sherry over chicken and bake 30 more minutes.
Cheese will soften, but will not melt.

title: rose's pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine margarine and sugar until well blended.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add next 5 ingredients and blend.
Spice will then be well mixed into batter.
Add pie filling and flour. Blend.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine buttermilk, sugar, shortening and salt.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese together.
Place half meat mixture in casserole dish.
Make a well in mixture.
Place cheese in the well and put remaining meat on top.
Seal meat together around edges and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Use large Dutch oven.
Brown meat in margarine.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, mix and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Reduce heat and cover, stirring often.
Simmer until potatoes are done.
Serve with cornbread.

title: buttermilk pie
