directions: Mix sugar with 1 1/2 cups milk in saucepan; bring to boil. Mix egg yolks, cornstarch and flour together with rest of milk. Add to other milk mixture when it boils, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together; chill and serve.

title: pepparkakor
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and syrup and mix together well.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Chill.
Roll very thin.
Make sure you have the rolling pin and area floured.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Cut cookies with a heart shaped cutter.

title: crisco frosting for cake
directions: Mix flour, milk and salt.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature.
Cream together Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and beat until smooth.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add salt, baking soda, cream of tartar and flour; mix well.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar with cinnamon in a separate bowl.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: date filled  ice box cookies
directions: Variations:
ginger, nuts, raisins or chocolate can be added.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour
in
pie shells.
Cook 10 minutes at 450°.
Cook 25 or 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: fruit bowl supreme
directions: *Or use 1 (16 ounce) can fruit cocktail, well drained.

title: barbecue corn
directions: Husk corn and remove silk.
Place each ear on a double thick sheet of foil.
Melt butter or margarine in a small pan; stir in barbecue sauce, salt and pepper.
Brush over corn.
Wrap corn in foil; twist ends to seal and place in large shallow pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, turning often.
Serve from foil wrappers.
To cook corn outdoors, place foil wrapped ears on grill over hot coals.
Grill 15 to 25 minutes, turning often.

title: family style oven potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain.
Saute onions in butter until golden.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix onions and half of pimento with potatoes.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining pimento, cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Serves 6.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil the chicken and debone. Save 3/4 cup broth.
Boil the broccoli spears as directed.
Line bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 can biscuits.
Alternate layer of chicken, then broccoli. Mix the soup with the broth. Add juice of 1/2 lemon and dash of Tabasco sauce.
Pour this over chicken mixture. Top with remaining biscuits and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: antipasto bowl
directions: Steam asparagus, covered for 2 minutes.
Drain and plunge into ice water.
Drain well.
Combine the asparagus, mushrooms, and the next 5 ingredients (mushrooms through pepperoncini peppers) in a large bowl.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add sauce and water after draining any fat; set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and pepper; set aside.

title: mom's home made catsup
directions: Heat tomato juice in large sauce pan to boiling.
Add vinegar.
Mix sugar, flour, salt pepper and cinnamon.
Slowly add to juice mixture.
May need to whisk to prevent lumps.
We use on meat loaf, scrambled eggs, baked beans.

title: basic microwave brownies
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Add butter and beat until blended.
Mix in flour and cocoa.
Stir in nuts. Spread evenly in 8-inch microwave dish.
Cook on High 6 to 7 minutes.
When done, top looks dry and will spring back when lightly touched.
Cool.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Cook sausage with chopped onions. Drain.
Mix sausage and onion mixture with soups, chicken and cooked rice.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: white fruit salad
directions: Add to the eggs the sugar and vinegar. Cook in double boiler until thick. Add the marshmallows and gelatine.
Remove from fire and stir until marshmallows begin to melt.
Add the cans of fruit, undrained, the nuts and the whipped cream.
Let chill in refrigerator (not freezer).
Slice and serve as salad on lettuce or as dessert with whipped cream.

title: barbecued beef
directions: In a Dutch oven or roasting pan with tight fitting cover, mix together all ingredients except meat.
Mix well.
Trim fat from meat and place meat in sauce.
Spoon sauce over meat; cover tightly and place in preheated 350° oven.
Roast 4 to 6 hours, depending on size of roast.
Remove meat from pan, discard any bone or fat. Shred meat with 2 forks and then return to sauce, stir.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in flat baking dish.
Mix half of the soup and water with rice and place on bottom of flat baking dish.
Lay chicken breasts on rice. Cover with rest of soup mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Put all the ingredients plus 5 cups of water in an electric slow-cooker, cover and cook on low for 12 to 14 hours, regulating the heat to maintain an almost simmer.
(Or cook in a tightly covered casserole in a 225° oven.
Add a little boiling water if the beans begin to look dry.)
They are done when they turn a dark reddish caramel brown.
Correct the seasoning before serving.

title: pineapple side dish
directions: Mix diced bread with other ingredients.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove cover and bake for 10 minutes more or until slightly brown on top.

title: never fail doughnuts
directions: Add ingredients in order given.
These are nice and soft and do not soak fat.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and add onion and garlic.
Stir the meat while it is cooking so it will crumble.
Drain the fat and place the meat in a slow cooker.
Add the remaining ingredient and simmer at 200° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
The slow cooker can be left uncovered during this time, or lid can be left slightly ajar. Stir meat and ingredients occasionally during the process of cooking.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Cook, stirring frequently until little of mixture forms very soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add caramels and vanilla.
Beat until caramels are melted and icing is of spreading consistency.

title: golden mushroom roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in covered baking dish or roaster.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour can of soup over.
Add onions.
Place in oven.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in oil, eggs and apples. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes in a greased 7 x 11 inch pan.
Serves 15.

title: garbage pail punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in 5-gallon bucket.
I usually put a large plastic garbage bag in bucket first.
Put in icebox to ferment for 1 day before serving.
Add 1 bag of ice on day of serving.
Keep covered.
Ideal for outdoor parties.
Not recommended for children.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and add 4 or 5 slices cheese on top.
Return to oven and cook 4 or 5 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: christmas coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cream butter and sugar.
Slowly add egg yolks and beat well.
Add yeast mixture to batter.
Combine flour and salt.
Beat slowly into the batter, alternating with the scalded milk.
Coat raisins in flour to prevent "sinking" in batter.
Add raisins and almonds to batter.
Divide into three 1 1/2-quart tube pans.
Each pan should be 1/2 full.
To rise, cover and let sit in a warm place for 3 hours.
Batter will almost double in size.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove cakes from the pans and sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Yield:
3 pans.

title: rye pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage and hamburger. Stir in cheese until melted, then add the Worcestershire sauce and oregano flakes. Place on rye bread squares.
Heat at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes. Can be frozen before baking.
Heat and eat.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Add prepared vegetables (salt and pepper to taste).
Cover with soup.
Top with prepared corn bread mix and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes, at 350° or until vegetables are tender.
(I use a 4-quart casserole dish to bake this in.)

title: layered salad
directions: Fill bowl 3/4 full with lettuce or spinach.
Layer English peas, water chestnuts, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Cover top with Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar over top and keep in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, crumble bacon over top.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring salted water to rolling boil and slowly stir in grits. Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine and garlic cheese.
Put eggs in a cup and add milk to make 1-cup measure.
Beat well and add to grits mixture.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole at 300° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cucumbers with laban(cucumber with yogurt)
directions: Crush garlic with salt and mint.
Peel and cut cucumbers into slices.
Add laban to cucumbers, garlic and dried mint mixture. Stir well and chill before serving.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet. Drain off any grease. Combine other ingredients; mix well.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: goobs
directions: Allow Cheez Whiz and ground chuck to reach room temperature. Mix in bowl and spread generously onto bread.
Place bread on a cookie sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 17 minutes or until meat is done.
Serve while warm.

title: hamburger cheese casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Sprinkle with garlic powder lightly.
Slice onion and potatoes thinly.
Boil in water until almost done.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer potatoes, meat, onion, cheese and soup, mixed with 1/4 can water.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Put rice on bottom of pan. Mix together soups, water and onion.
Top rice with soup mixture. Put chicken on top of soup mixture, skin side up.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Add vinegar to milk, then add flour, salt and shortening. This crust can be handled more than usual and still come out flaky light. Will also keep in refrigerator several days.

title: house shrimp dip
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Coarsely chop shrimp.
In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Makes 3 cups of dip.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream and bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pecan pieces and stir until sugary and well coated.
Put on wax paper to dry, separate after cooling.

title: oven rice pilaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together water, butter or margarine, bouillon granules and thyme. Microwave on High (100% power) 3 to 4 minutes to bring to boil. Stir to dissolve bouillon granules.
Stir in rice, carrot and onion.
Cover tightly.
Bake 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 15 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: christian's seafood stew
directions: In large kettle or pot brown all ingredients except flour, dressing and water.
Cook approximately 15 minutes.
Mix flour, water and salad dressing together, add to stew and cook for another 15 to 20 minutes.
And there you have it!!!!!!

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan with sliced peaches.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
In a bowl, combine butter, sugar, flour, egg, walnuts and salt.
Spoon over apples (batter will be thick).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour 18 muffin cups.
In a large bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in carrots, apples, raisins, coconut and nuts.
In a medium size bowl, whisk together the eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to the dry ingredients and stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into the prepared muffin cups and bake for about 20 minutes or until tops are golden and spring back when lightly pressed.
Contains 16 gr fat.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in bowl and mix at once.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: oreo pie
directions: Set aside 12 Oreos; crush remaining Oreos.
Lightly spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray; press crushed Oreos into bottom of pan.
Slice ice cream and arrange on top of crushed Oreos to form second layer.
Top ice cream with syrup/fudge; spread whipping cream over syrup/fudge.
Crush the set aside 12 Oreos and layer over whipping cream.

title: meat loaf italiana
directions: Blend 1 teaspoon parsley with mashed potatoes.
Mix meat, bread crumbs, water, parsley, grated cheese, eggs, onion, salt and pepper very thoroughly.
Brush bread pan or baking dish with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Sprinkle lightly with 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Place half of the meat mixture in dish.
Alternate with layers of meat, Mozzarella cheese and potatoes.
Top with balance of meat.
Close edges firmly so potatoes won't ooze out.
Brush with balance of olive oil. Bake in a 350° oven for 85 minutes or until top is golden brown, but not dry.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion until tender.
Add flour, milk and butter.
Cook on medium heat to boil and until flour is dissolved.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk, vinegar and mustard.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.

title: pecan-cheese crackers
directions: Cream butter and cheese together until well blended.
Add flour and pepper; mix thoroughly.
Add chopped pecans.
Shape into rolls, refrigerate 1 hour and cut 1/4-inch thick.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: sunday supper casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Saute onion in melted oleo about 3 minutes. Add soup and milk.
Heat.
Sprinkle half of the dry stuffing mix into baking dish.
Top with broccoli, then with chicken.
Pour liquid over, then top with remaining dry mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spread about 1/3 of the potatoes in loose, overlapping fashion in a greased baking dish, about 2 1/2-quart capacity.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with tablespoon of butter or margarine, cut in small bits.
Repeat with another layer of potatoes, flour, salt, pepper and butter or margarine.
Cover with remaining potatoes and dot with remaining butter or margarine. Pour milk over top.

title: san francisco salad
directions: Cook rice and cool.
Add all the chopped ingredients.
Mix well.
Save a small amount of the marinade and mix with mayonnaise. Pour over rice mix and stir well.
Chill and serve.
Looks great served with a leaf of lettuce on a salad plate.

title: burger, vegies and potato-one dish meal
directions: Put in layers as listed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour in a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Sift the flour, salt and sugar together.
Cut in the Crisco shortening with a pastry blender.
(I do it the old-fashioned way with my hands.)
Beat the egg in a small bowl.
Add the vinegar to the beaten egg.
Pour the egg and vinegar mixture in the bowl containing the flour and shortening mixture.
Add the water, a little at a time, until you get the right consistency.
Mix thoroughly.

title: "stove top" rice pudding
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot, except vanilla.
Get to rolling boil on high heat.
Reduce to low, steady simmer.
Cook for about 1 hour or until mixture gets thick.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into bowl and sprinkle with nutmeg. You may want to add a little more sugar for those with a "sweet tooth."

title: stir-fry turkey leftovers
directions: In a large skillet, saute vegetables and onion in oil for 6 to 8 minutes until crisp-tender.
Combine stir-fry sauce and turkey. Add to vegetable mixture; heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: blender banana bread
directions: Put eggs, butter and bananas in blender and cream.
Add sugar; blend.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts; mix with a spoon.
Pour into a greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: barbecue marinade
directions: Rub this
into both sides of pork chops and refrigerate a minimum of 8 hours before cooking.
Keep balance of marinade in closed
jar.
This keeps indefinitely if refrigerated.
It will do about 60 chops.

title: rhubarb spread
directions: Put rhubarb and sugar together; let stand overnight.
It will make its own juice.
Stir occasionally.
The next morning, put on stove and boil 5 minutes.
Take from stove and stir in jello.
(You can also use 3 cups rhubarb with 2 cups strawberries in place of 5 cups rhubarb.)

title: laramie tarts
directions: Mix pie crust according to directions and add poppy seed. Press walnut-size piece of dough into small size muffin tins.
Mix Swiss cheese, salami and green onions.
Put in pastry shells. Beat in eggs and add sour cream, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Stir and put 1 tablespoon over contents in pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 36.
These appetizers freeze well.
Reheat 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, using pineapple juice for liquid in cake.
Add water to make up required liquid on package. Bake 20 minutes at 350° in well-greased and floured pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Cool in pan.
Blend together other ingredients until smooth.
Fold in pineapple.
Spread over top of cooled cake.
Top with large size Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut. Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: crissy's summer gazpacho
directions: Chill a large glass bowl in preparation for the gazpacho. This really does seem to make a difference.
Combine liquids, salts and pepper.
Add tomatoes, cucumber, pepper and onions to liquid.
Garnish with spring onion slices if you like or use your own garnish idea.

title: company pleasin potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, eggs, onions, pimientos and seasonings.
Add combined salad dressing and mustard.
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and add 1 teaspoon soda; let cool.
Cream the shortening, 1 cup sugar and beaten eggs.
Add to cooled date mixture.
Add the vanilla.
Stir flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to batter and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix chocolate chips, sugar and nuts together.
Sprinkle over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream and a cherry on top of each piece of cake.

title: frosty fruit shake
directions: Place milk and Marshmallow Creme in blender container.
Cover. Process until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: zelje(sauerkraut)
directions: Cover the kraut with water and boil for 25 minutes.
Pour off the water and sprinkle with flour.
Stir well and cook a little longer.
Serve with pork cracklings or crumbled bacon.
Kraut may be seasoned with 1 to 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon caraway or celery seed.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add green pepper, onion, tomato sauce and same size can of water.
Add Minute rice.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge pops
directions: You also need wooden sticks or plastic spoons.

title: vegetable casserole(stag night potatoes)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Mix together next 7 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: maple custard
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into individual custard cups. Set the cups in a pan of warm water and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for about 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center of the custards comes out clean.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with oranges and pineapple.
Mix in all the rest of the ingredients and chill.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and oleo.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add to corn; mix well.
Fry in hot fat on both sides until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve at once with syrup.

title: chicken pecan quiche
directions: Mix well and press into deep-dish 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Cool completely.

title: burger bundles
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and form into 2-inch balls and pat into 4-inch circle.
Combine next three ingredients and set aside.
Make up Stove Top stuffing according to directions.
Place a scoop full in the middle of hamburger circle and bring hamburger up around stuffing.
Place in a baking dish and pour soup mixture over hamburger bundles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can also pat hamburger into bottom of pan; add stuffing over and pour soup over the stuffing, then bake.

title: pineapple honey cake
directions: Cream shortening and honey.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with juice and vanilla.
Bake in angel food cake pan at 300° for 1 hour or until toothpick is inserted and comes out
dry.

title: squirrel stew
directions: In a plastic bag or on a plate, mix together flour, salt, pepper and parsley.
Dredge squirrel pieces.
Preheat oven to 350°. In a skillet, heat oil and brown squirrel, a few pieces at a time. Remove with slotted spoon and place in a roasting pan or Dutch oven.
Place onions, carrots and potatoes over rabbit.
Sprinkle with herbs and add orange zest and bay leaves.
Pour in red wine and tomatoes.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until squirrel is fork-tender.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix and cocoa.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, food coloring, margarine and eggs.
Blend until moistened.
Add soda and vinegar, then beat for 4 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fritter away your time (fish)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry in canola oil (unsaturated fat).
They can also be baked in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes to reduce fat further.
Serve with green salad and large steak fries.
The second ingredient is grits which makes them crunchy.

title: freezer rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening. Dissolve dry yeast in warm water. Add with buttermilk to dry ingredients. Mix well. Turn out on floured board and cut out. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: crem fraiche
directions: In a small bowl, stir together whipping cream and dairy sour cream. Cover with plastic wrap. Let stand at room temperature for 2 to 5 hours or until mixture thickens. When thickened, cover and chill in the refrigerator until serving time or up to 48 hours. Stir before serving. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: surprise meringues
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla together until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating until peaks are stiff.
Fold in chocolate bits and nuts.
Cover cookie sheet with plain paper.
Drop cookies on by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cool; remove from paper.

title: seed cakes queen biscuits
directions: Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Mix all ingredients.
More flour will be needed to work.
Roll into strips and into 1-inch pieces. Roll into sesame seed before baking.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add shortening, vanilla and 2/3 cup milk; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1/4 cup milk; beat 2 minutes longer.
Add berries and mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: cheese soup for a crowd
directions: Cook carrots, celery and onions in chicken stock until tender. Heat milk and add vegetables.
Add a paste made of oleo and cornstarch.
Slowly add the cheese.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Tabasco.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix with hands until well blended.
Shape into rolls and chill.
Rolls can be rolled into finely chopped nuts or paprika before chilling.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: ellen's enchilada stacks
directions: To start with, put 2 tablespoons shortening in a pan and heat. In another pan, put the mild enchilada sauce.
Dip the corn tortillas in the pan of heated shortening, then take out and dip into pan of heated enchilada sauce.
From there, put into another pan and sprinkle with cheese and onions.
Top each tortilla with some of the enchilada sauce.
Do this with each tortilla.
I usually make 2 stacks.
If any sauce is left, I pour over tops of both stacks.

title: northern bean casserole
directions: Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Mix all together. Bake uncovered at 275° until most liquid is cooked away.
I usually add some bacon at the end.

title: hawkeye corn fritters
directions: Add corn and all dry ingredients which have been sifted together. Beat the egg, milk and shortening together. Pour into the corn mixture and mix very well. Drop from a teaspoon into hot shortening and fry until golden brown on all sides. (Should look like hush puppies.)
Drain on absorbent towel and serve piping hot with powdered sugar sprinkled over them.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef with onion. Drain off grease. Put all ingredients in Dutch oven and simmer until cabbage is tender. Stir to mix.

title: chocolate coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and coconut.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir in vanilla and milk. Add melted margarine, then coconut.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with Doritos.
Pour in soups and tomatoes, mixed together, over chicken, cut in bite size pieces. Grate cheese and cover top.
Put Doritos in top and on sides.
Bake at 350°.

title: very rich and good chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk a little at a time until well blended.
Add egg yolks; cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into two 9-inch baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites for meringue.
Brown top of meringue.

title: salmon spread
directions: In food processor (or by hand), blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and dill until smooth.
Add salmon and green onions and process very briefly just to mix.
The salmon and onion chunks should be visible and the cream cheese mixture still white.
Chill.
Serve with hearty crackers.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Combine all but last 2 ingredients and boil.
Let cool.
Add soda and flour.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine thawed potatoes and 1/2 cup butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except topping. Bake in buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Make topping; cover top of potatoes with mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove 1 hour before baking, if stored in refrigerator.
Can be made well ahead.

title: hello dollies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine and cracker crumbs. Spread in a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Layer the nuts, chocolate chips, and coconut over the crumbs.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over entire pan of ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix macaroni, mayonnaise, pimiento, cheese, onion and soup. Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crumble 1 roll Ritz crackers over top.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until crackers are brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add onion.
Stir in milk and egg.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot fat until brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Combine
vegetable
oil, vinegar, lemon juice, salt and mustard in a small mixing bowl, stirring well.
Place tomatoes in a
medium
bowl;
add
marinade.
Top with onion slices and parsley.
Cover
bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Yields about 6 to 8 servings.

title: refrigerator (raisin) bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and shortening; stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
(Will keep 5 to 6 weeks.)
When ready to bake, spoon batter into greased muffin tins 2/3 full for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: calico meringues
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually add sugar to make meringues stiff.
Fold in M&M's.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Let cool on cookie sheet.
Remove from cookie sheet and store in container with tight lid.

title: coconut black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well. Combine sugar, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts, coconut and flavoring.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Pour hot coconut syrup over hot cake.
Allow cake to remain in pan 4 hours to absorb syrup.
Wrap well; cake will be very moist.

title: russian cabbage soup
directions: Shred cabbage; discard core.
Chop onions; cook over medium heat for 15 minutes with the butter.
Sprinkle with flour. Dissolve the bouillon cubes in the water; gradually add to the cabbage and onion mixture.
Stir constantly until it reaches boiling point.
Add all remaining ingredients, except sour cream. Cover; cook over low heat for 1 hour.
(Serve garnished with sour cream; optional.)

title: ranch fajitas
directions: Cut steak into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Brown in a nonstick skillet for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in pepper strips and cook 1 to 2 more minutes.
Stir in Ranch salad dressing mix and water.
Cook 1 minute and serve in warm flour tortillas.
Serves 4.

title: auntie claire's brownie pie
directions: Sprinkle nuts in pie shell.
Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Combine corn syrup, sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla in bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Pour over nuts. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sausage and cheese casserole
directions: Cut
one
package
of
sausage
into
bite size chunks. Brown in skillet with onions, oil and bell peppers.
Place in casserole dish
with
cream of mushroom soup, rice and water. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake until cheese melts, approximately 5 minutes.

title: cooked fudge icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together except vanilla.
Boil hard 1 minute and stir to prevent burning.
Add vanilla and beat until cool enough to spread on warm cake.
This icing thickens fast as it cools.

title: luscious lime pie
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and salt. In mixing bowl, with wooden spoon, mix egg yolks, lime juice and water.
Add to saucepan and mix well.
Over medium heat, cook and stir just until mixture comes to full boil.
The mixture will have started thickening.

title: orange blush
directions: Combine orange juice, cranberry juice and sugar.
Chill.
Just before serving, stir in sparkling water.
Pour over crushed ice in old-fashioned chilled glasses.
Makes 6 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice and add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Stir in whipped topping and pour into 9-inch pie shells.
Can be sprinkled with coconut.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: parmesan popovers
directions: Place oven rack on next to lowest shelf.
Grease 6 deep muffin or custard cups and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; set aside.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add soups, water and rice.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the graham crackers with 1 stick of butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and 2 sticks butter.
Beat 15 minutes.
Spread over cracker crust.
Slice bananas and place over filling.
Sprinkle drained pineapple on top of bananas and top with Cool Whip.
Decorate top with cherries and nuts.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Combine any remaining ingredients. Put in crock-pot and add water to consistency you want.

title: beet jelly
directions: Clean beets really well.
Cook and save juice.
Strain through several layers of cheesecloth.
Bring to a hard boil the beet juice, lemon juice and Sure-Jell.
Boil for 5 minutes and then add the 8 cups sugar and raspberry jello.
Cook for 1 or 2 minutes or until jelly flakes off of a spoon.
Put into jars; wipe rims and seal as with any other jellies.

title: molded beet salad
directions: Make 2 cups liquid with juice from beets and 1/4 cup vinegar. Thinly slice beets.
Add cloves and bay leaf to liquid and heat to boiling.
Let stand a few minutes.
Strain liquid and add to lemon jello. Add sliced beets and sugar while hot.
Pour into molds. Good served with sweet and sour dressing.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cut up lots of Mozzarella cheese.
Stir all ingredients together.
Put in oven until cheese melts and bubbles a little.
It doesn't take long because it is already cooked and warm.

title: pecan sweet potatoes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and place in an 8-inch square casserole.

title: the very best deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks and press through sieve or mash fine with fork.
Combine yolks with other ingredients; beat until smooth.
Refill whites with fork or spoon.

title: simple fruit salad
directions: Cut up all fruit and mix together. Pour sugar on top of fruit mixture and refrigerate until ready to serve. Mix well and add pecans when ready to serve.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, combine potatoes, onions and asparagus.
Add milk.
Dot with butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Immediately before serving, lay cheese on top and let it melt slightly.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook butter, syrup and brown sugar 5 minutes.
Add milk.
Pour over popcorn.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soak yeast in water 5 minutes. Dissolve sugar and salt in milk. Add shortening, eggs, 1 cup flour and yeast. Beat until smooth. Add remaining flour to make soft dough. Knead on floured board until smooth. Place in greased bowl (grease top of dough). Let rise until double, 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Form dough into small pieces. Place in greased muffin pan. Brush with melted butter. Let rise 20 to 30 minutes. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Brush with butter. Makes 24.

title: crepes suzette
directions: First of all, make plain French pancakes like this:
sift flour in a bowl and break into this the eggs.
Add melted butter and salt; mix it well.
Pour in cold milk very gradually, mixing constantly for about 5 minutes.
Gently butter a frying pan and put it on the range; when it is hot, pour in batter to make 5-inch cake and after 2 minutes of cooking, turn it over and bake it on the other side, also, for 2 minutes.
Place the pancakes (you should have about a dozen) on a hot plate and cover them up and prepare your Crepes Suzette Sauce.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter at low heat, cool.
Beat egg, add sugar and flour; mix well.
Pour chocolate into sugar, vanilla and salt; stir until blended.
Flour and oil 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 17 minutes.
Will be undercooked.
Cool.
Cut into squares and powder with confectioners sugar.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine next 3 ingredients with 1/2 cup milk.
Add to creamed mixture.
Coat damp berries in 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons flour and fold into the batter.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 70 or 80 minutes or until done.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
This will take approximately 2 months.
Cut vegetables into cubes (another 2 months).
Place meat in pan and cover with 1,000 gallons of bacon gravy and simmer 4 weeks.
Shovel in salt and pepper to taste. When meat is tender, add vegetables.
(A steam shovel is useful for this.)
Simmer slowly for 4 more weeks.
Garnish with parsley. Will serve 3,000 people.
If more are expected, add the two rabbits.
This is not recommended, however, since very few people like hare in their stew!

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lean pork and rice veggie bake
directions: Brown meat on both sides in frying pan with Pam.
Add next 5 ingredients to pan, stirring constantly for 5 minutes at simmer. Then add dry gravy mixes, water and tomato sauce.
Simmer approximately 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place 1 layer of pork steak in 9 x 13 casserole, then layer of rice and vegetables.
Top layer to be steaks.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Meat will fall off bone and rice will be plump and moist.
Delicious!
Add applesauce and green beans and you have a great meal.
Makes 6 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Clean and cap persimmons (must be ripe and soft).
Run through a sieve.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bake in sheet pan or in layers at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Good with ice cream or Cool Whip while warm.

title: delicious pizza-flavored vegetable soup
directions: Place onion, garlic, undrained tomatoes, broth, water, salt, pepper and potatoes in a large soup pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add spaghetti or squash.
Boil, stirring occasionally, until spaghetti is tender, about 10 minutes.
Add beans and heat through.
Gradually add cheese 2 tablespoons at a time, stirring after each addition.
In a blender, process remaining ingredients until smooth, adding 1 tablespoon water if needed.
Pour this mixture into the soup and stir.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Mix one cup boiling water and Jell-O; mix.
Pour in orange juice, pineapple and drained oranges.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in refrigerator until jelled.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put into greased round baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies; put half of the crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and oleo until smooth.
Add powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
After mixing well, combine with cream cheese mixture.
Pour over crumbs in pan.
Put rest of crumbs on top. Chill in refrigerator.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Pour juice of clams in top of double boiler.
Add cream cheese and Old English cheese.
Melt and add Worcestershire sauce and clams.
Serve in chafing dish.
Can be reheated and holds its consistency.

title: pineapple turnover biscuits
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, butter and cinnamon and divide in 10 muffin cups.
Center each with a walnut half.
Add 1 teaspoon pineapple syrup to each cup and top with a biscuit.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°; remove from oven and invert immediately on serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: tostada pizza
directions: Bake 10 more minutes or until bubbly.
Top with lettuce, tomato, sour cream, etc.
Serves 4 to 6 main dishes, 12 or more appetizer servings.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in tomatoes, salt, oregano, parsley, garlic salt and pepper.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add zucchini and simmer 10 more minutes or until zucchini is tender.
(I use fresh broccoli as a substitute for zucchini.)

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: Beat above 3 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Batter will be thin.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° or 375° for one hour. Seems better if frozen a while.
M - mmm good!

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Put chicken in dish for oven.
Warm tomatoes, add cornstarch and seasonings.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Sprinkle with Parmesan and serve.

title: cinnamon coffee cake(quick bread)
directions: Combine flour, sugars, oil, 2 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, ginger and salt; mix well.
Combine 1/2 cup flour mixture, walnuts and remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Set aside.
Add buttermilk, egg, baking powder and soda to remaining flour mixture.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle reserved nut mixture over top.
Bake in 350° gas oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: homemade dill pickles
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Fit cukes into 2 one-quart jars; pour in enough of vinegar to cover cukes.
Tighten lids and refrigerate at least 1 week before serving to develop flavor.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Put
all
into	blender
on
"blend"
speed.
Pour into graham cracker
crust
and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.	Top with prepared pie filling (cherry or blueberry) when cooled.

title: jello cranberry
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Add sugar and let stand 2 hours.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water and when cool, add pineapple, nuts and cranberry mixture.
Let stand to thicken.

title: pecan cake
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Sift salt, flour and baking powder together.
Separate eggs and beat yolks until creamy.
Beat whites until stiff.
Cream butter and brown sugar. Add yolks; mix well.
Dissolve coffee in hot water; mix with milk and vanilla.
Add alternately with dry ingredients, mixing well. Fold in pecans and egg whites.
Bake in oiled and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Mix all ingredients. Let rise until light.
Punch down.
Make into rolls; let rise again.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: peanut butter granola
directions: Combine oats, sesame seed and wheat germ in a large bowl. Beat together oil, honey and peanut butter.
Add to oat mixture, blending well.
Spread over bottom of greased jelly roll pan. Bake in a 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Loosen, but cool in pan.
Store in sealed container in refrigerator.
Serve with milk.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: holiday macaroons
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar slowly and beat until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar and eggs.
Beat in butter, vanilla, lemon rind and coconut.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix in blender.
Store in moisture proof container.
Use 3 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Enjoy!

title: summer lime chicken breastshouston, texas
directions: Trim fat from chicken breasts and pound thin between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Combine olive oil, lime juice, garlic, 2 Tbsp. cilantro, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Pour over the chicken and marinate for at least 1 hour.
Grill or broil the chicken breasts for 2 minutes on each side.
Remove to a platter.
Sprinkle with remaining cilantro and serve with roasted red and yellow peppers.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: This recipe works best if using a black iron skillet.

title: chicken soup and rice
directions: In a large Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Season chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Brown well in margarine.
Remove browned pieces.
In drippings, saute onions, carrots, garlic, celery and green onions until soft.
Add other ingredients except rice.
Cook, covered, on low for about 15 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add water if necessary.
Soup should be thick.

title: amazing coconut pie(just mix, bake and serve)
directions: Combine milk, sugar and Bisquick.
Mix eggs, butter (room temperature).
Add vanilla in electric blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie dish.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: sesame seed pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt together. Cut shortening into the flour mixture and add the sesame seeds. Add ice water and blend gently with a fork until thoroughly moistened. Roll out pastry and place in a 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Great for entree or dessert pies.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and butter. Pat half this mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a saucepan, mix together sugar, salt, cornstarch and water. Cook until thickened. Add vanilla and butter. Pare apples (I use 4 cups of apples); slice thin and add to cooked mixture, tossing lightly to mix. Spread evenly over crumbs. Pat remaining crumbs over apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: meringue shells
directions: Early in the day, or up to 5 hours ahead, preheat oven to 200°.
Have egg whites at room temperature.
In small bowl, beat egg whites at highest speed with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually sprinkle in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition for about 2 minutes, or until sugar is completely dissolved.
To test, rub meringue between fingers.
If grainy, continue beating.
It takes about 15 minutes to beat in all sugar.
Add vanilla and continue beating at high speed until mixture stands in stiff, glossy peaks.
Put into pie plate, smoothing it at the center and piling it high on the sides to form a shell.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Blend 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon
in
saucepan.
Stir
in
water
and
bring to a boil, stirring
constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and peaches. Pour
into a shallow baking dish.
Combine biscuit mix and 2 tablespoons of remaining sugar.
Blend in cream.
Drop dough in
6 mounds
around edge of baking dish.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and orange peel.
Sprinkle on dough.
Bake 25 minutes
or
until
peaches
are tender and biscuits are golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: lenore's angel
directions: Follow directions for angel cake on box.
Let cool completely. Cut up in 1-inch squares and put in bowl.

Layer the following: light layer of Cool Whip, thick layer of bananas, light layer of Cool Whip, light layer of angel food cake, light layer of Cool Whip, thick layer of strawberries, light layer of Cool Whip and the rest of the bananas and strawberries.
Include cherries on top layer.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except sour cream.
Pour half of mixture in bowl and set in refrigerator until firm.
Carefully spread sour cream on top of firm mixture, then pour other half over sour cream and set in refrigerator until firm.
The second half should remain at room temperature until added.
This is really pretty in a clear glass bowl.

title: fair layer salad dessert
directions: Mix and press the first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
(This crust without nuts is good for cream pies.)
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and pour over first mixture.
Chill.
Beat pudding mix into milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour over second mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Chill.

title: chicken feed
directions: Mix in a bowl the peanuts, sunflower seeds, raisins and M&M's. Add Cheerios; stir gently.
Serve in paper cups or small bags.
A great snack to take along on a walk or hike.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Put flour, cocoa and sugar in a skillet and add milk.
Cook until it thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: hershey bar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add syrup and melted candy.
Add salt to flour and soda to buttermilk; add to other ingredients.
Add vanilla and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8-inch square pan.
Blend until crumbly, the brown sugar, sifted flour, rolled oats, cinnamon, nutmeg and soft butter.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, until apples are tender and topping is golden brown. Serve warm with cream, ice cream or hard sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla. Stir oats, flour, soda and 1 teaspoon salt; stir into creamed mixture until blended.
Set aside.

title: low-fat pot roast
directions: Place meat, onions,
garlic,
carrots
and
potatoes in large roasting pan.
Cover with canned tomatoes, tomato sauce, soy sauce, Worcestershire
sauce
and
stock.
Sprinkle
with pepper and basil.	Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until done.

title: garlic butter chips
directions: Preheat ovent to 350°.
Saute garlic in butter.
Remove garlic. with garlic butter.
Place on baking sheet lined with paper towels.
Heat 5 minutes; drain on clean paper towels, if desired.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and bacon.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy macaroni salad
directions: Cook 1 1/2 to 2 cups elbow macaroni in 4 quarts boiling water. Drain and rinse using cold water.
Cut cheese into approximately 1/4-inch cubes.
Add the equal amounts of cheese, onion and celery.
Sprinkle about 1/2 of the garlic salt.
Pepper to taste and to add color, if desired.
Mix well with the Hellmann's mayonnaise; taste and add more garlic salt to bring out flavor. Any mayonnaise or salad dressing may be used, but it tastes better with Hellmann's.

title: rosie's cheese ball
directions: When cream cheese is very soft, add all ingredients except walnuts.
You may find that the green peppers are diced easily with a food processor or blender.
Mix ingredients well with a spoon or hand.
Shape into a large ball and roll in crushed walnuts.
Chill approximately 1 hour.
Place on platter with crackers.

title: cornflake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry.
Fold in sugar gradually.
Add vanilla, coconut, cornflakes and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until delicate brown at 375°.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Put egg, vinegar, mustard and salt in blender with 1/4 cup of oil.
Cover and blend about 5 seconds.
Without stopping blender, gradually add remaining oil.
Put in covered container and refrigerate.
Fresh dill weed is a nice addition.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix together in order given.
Spoon into greased skillet. Cook until brown.
Turn and cook other side.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together and press into an oblong pan.
Cook 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan (round or square) and bake according to package directions.
The cookie dough should be light brown.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon juice with spoon until lumps disappear.
Spread on cooled cookie crust and top with sliced fruits of your choice (strawberries, kiwi, bananas, pineapple, blueberries, apples, star fruit and/or fresh peaches) arranged in rows.
Use 4 or more fruits and combine different colored ones.
If using sliced bananas, put them in a bowl and sprinkle with lemon juice before putting on pizza; this will keep them from turning brown.
Refrigerate pizza and slice when ready to serve.

title: sparkling shower punch
directions: Mix sugar and water together in a heavy saucepan. Set over low heat and stir until sugar is dissolved. Increase heat, cover and boil 5 minutes. Cool and chill.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Put in Ragu sauce; simmer 20 minutes.
Cook lasagne.
Layer sauce first.
Pour in enough to cover bottom of dish (9 x 13-inch).
Arrange 3 lasagne strips over sauce.
Add layer of Mozzarella.
Repeat.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, about 1 hour.

title: firehouse spaghetti
directions: Brown ground chuck, sausage, onions, green pepper and mushrooms. Combine with seasonings, except sugar. Add tomato and Prego sauces, then add sugar. Bring to boil and simmer for a minimum of 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add water for desired consistency. Serve over cooked spaghetti. Serves 6.

title: zucchini orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottoms only of two 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in oil, 2/3 cup orange juice and zucchini.
Stir in remaining bread ingredients; mix well. Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool slightly.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Drain.
Add sauce, salt and spices. Place half cabbage in greased casserole.
Top with meat sauce. Repeat.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well; pat firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over top.
Put into warm oven only long enough to melt bits, 3 or 4 minutes, then spread over crumb mixture.
Cool and cut.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
Melt butter in 3-quart pan. Blend in flour and stir until smooth.
Slowly stir in chicken broth and pepper and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add milk and cook slowly, stirring constantly until thickened.
Do not boil.
Add crabmeat to milk mixture and salt to taste.
Remove from heat and serve.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together, except cheese and potato chips, and pour into a baking dish.
Mix cheese and crushed potato chips and sprinkle on top.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: angie's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix broccoli, carrots, peppers, rice, chopped onion and 1/2 of fried onions and place in large baking dish.
Pour milk soup mixture over.
Place Cheez Whiz in piles on top.
Then add rest of fried onions.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, cook onions, covered in butter, about 20 to 25 minutes, until tender.
Add beef broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; bring to a rolling boil.
Cover, reduce heat and cook 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Serve with large toasted French bread cubes, topped with Swiss or Jack cheese, and enjoy!!!

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut flowerets of broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces. Place in a large bowl.
Add bacon crumbles, onion, raisins, and cheese.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Add to the broccoli/cauliflower mixture and toss gently.

title: french pie
directions: Melt butter and unsweetened chocolate on low heat.
In another bowl, beat until light the eggs.
Blend in Karo syrup.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture to bowl and mix together. Pour over pie crust and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pie is crusty and filling soft like custard.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut butter and chocolate pie
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter; press on bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or a 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
In medium saucepan, combine pudding mix and milk.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil; remove from heat.
Pour 2 cups hot pudding into small bowl and add peanut butter chips.
Stir until melted and smooth.

title: squash casserole(from the files of charlie mae williams)
directions: Cook squash and onion in water and salt until tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Crumble Ritz crackers and saute in butter.
Drain squash.
Put in buttered dish in layers with cheese.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hamburger oriental
directions: Saute lightly chopped celery and onions in butter.
Fry in separate pan hamburger and rice.
Add hamburger mixture to celery and onions.
Mix together remaining ingredients except bean sprouts, then add along with the bean sprouts to hamburger mixture.
Heat.
Serve over Chinese noodles.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Knead together.
Add a little more flour if needed, until dough is not sticky.
Pinch off; shape by hand into biscuits, about 1/2-inch thick.
Place in greased baking pan.
Bake at 475° until just starting to turn light brown.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Arrange the carrots, green pepper and onions in 3 layers. Bring the remaining ingredients to a boil, stirring gently.
Pour the ingredients over the salad.
Place the dish in the refrigerator for 12 hours before serving.

title: three vegetable casserole
directions: Remove vegetables from packages in frozen state.
When partially thawed, break into buttered casserole.
Pour soup over. Top with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, butter, syrup and salt in saucepan and heat until it bubbles.
Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add baking soda until foamy, then add the popped popcorn.
Mix until the popped corn is coated, then divide into two 9 x 13-inch pans and bake for 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: hot curried chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, curry powder and salt; mix well. Add remaining ingredients, except the almonds. Spoon into an ungreased 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake 20 minutes or until hot through. Serves 4.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook vegetable; drain.
Place in shallow 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir in soup; blend in milk.
Pour over vegetable. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot. Garnish with bacon before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: purple cows
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth and frothy. Makes 2 servings.

title: cheddar spinach pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toss cheese with flour.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Add cheese mixture and spinach.
Mix well. Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: finger paint
directions: Dissolve elastic starch in cold water.
Smooth out lumps and add boiling water.
Stir constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens, but do not boil for more than 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: dillon's slaw(make one day ahead of serving.)
directions: Microwave sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt, mustard and celery for 5 minutes. Mix cabbage and onion. Pour mixture over cabbage and onions. Refrigerate for 1 day before serving. Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: oreo cups
directions: Line muffin tin with baking cups.
Twist Oreo cookies apart, place frosting side up in cup.
Crush unfrosted side and save. Mix next 4 ingredients and fill cups.
Sprinkle unfrosted pieces over filling.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Melt next 2 ingredients and drizzle over tops (pour into baggie and snip a corner off).
Sprinkle peppermint candy over drizzled chocolate. Refrigerate.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla.
Then add flour a little at a time.
Then add pecans. Shape into disc or drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels over hot water.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Mix well.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Serve.

title: tomato snacks (good!!)
directions: Spread Party Rye Bread with Miracle Whip or mayonnaise. Sprinkle with garlic powder, parmesan cheese. Place a thin slice of tomato on top and sprinkle with oregano.

title: low-fat baked fish
directions: Dip fish in (or spread on) yogurt.
Cover with bread crumbs. Place on baking rack and bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Turn over and bake for another 5 minutes or until done.

title: sweet cereal mix
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Boil margarine, brown sugar and Karo.
Bring to a boil.
Let bubble for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Stir.
Pour over cereal and mix.
Use two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Put in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Using a very small bowl or Pyrex cup, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix in other ingredients and mold in a pretty bowl to set.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add cheese and melt.
Add mushroom soup with 1/2 can milk.
Cook noodles according to package directions and mix together.
Pour into casserole and top with French fried onions. Bake in medium oven for 45 minutes.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in butter or margarine.
Place in baking dish.
Heat soup, thyme and water and mix well.
When blended, mix in sour cream, parsley flakes and 1/2 can French fried onions. Pour mixture over pork chops.
Bake at 350° in covered pan one hour.
Remove cover 5 minutes before serving, sprinkle on rest of onions and return to oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup cold water.
Boil 3/4 cup water.
Add sugar, cornstarch mix and 1/2 package strawberry Jell-O.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Let cool.
Pour over sliced strawberries in baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: marshmallow brownies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and cover with miniature marshmallows.
Put back in oven for 3 minutes.

title: cranberry festival salad
directions: Dissolve
gelatin
in
boiling
water.
Add cold water. Chill until thickened.
Cut orange in wedges and remove seeds. Put orange and cranberries through food grinder; mix in apple and sugar.
Fold into thickened gelatin.
Pour into 3 cup mold or individual
molds.
Chill
until firm.
Unmold on lettuce. Makes 6
servings.
Recipe
may
be doubled for shallow 1 1/2 quart mold.

title: lane cake
directions: Beat egg whites until they hold a peak, but not dry.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add butter and sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add beaten egg whites, salt and vanilla and make in 3 layers at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green tomato raspberry jam
directions: Squeeze and drain tomatoes until you have 4 cups.
Add sugar; stir and bring to a boil.
Boil for 7 minutes.
Add Jell-O; stir to dissolve sugar.
Put into hot jars.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes about 6 half pints.

title: brownie pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in heavy saucepan over low heat. Pour into medium size bowl and cool.
Add egg, sugar and corn syrup.
Beat with rotary blender until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° on lower shelf for 40 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: clam chowder
directions: Boil carrots and potatoes with just enough water to cover them. Do not drain. Add butter, whipping cream and 3/4 of half and half. Bring to a slight boil. Add drained clams. Boil. Add instant potatoes to thicken. If too thick, add half and half or milk. Salt and pepper.

title: chocolate frosted brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 9 x 2 inch square pan with shortening. Melt margarine and chocolate in 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly. Cool slightly. Beat sugar, vanilla and eggs in medium bowl on high speed for 5 minutes. Beat in chocolate mixture on low speed. Beat in flour just until blended. Stir in walnuts, if desired. Spread in pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or just until brownies begin to pull away from the sides of the pan. Cool completely before spreading with Chocolate Buttercream Frosting.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well and add to corn.
Melt butter and add to milk. Add spices.
Add to corn and eggs and stir well.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs. Bake in a very slow 250° oven for 40 to 60 minutes, until custard is set. (Knife stuck into the center will come out clean.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen banana trifle
directions: Peel bananas and wrap each in plastic wrap.
Place in freezer until frozen hard.
Remove bananas from freezer and puree in food processor until mixture resembles pudding or ice cream.
Place one layer of sponge cake in a trifle or similar serving dish.
Spoon on half of bananas, half ice cream and the remaining sponge layer. Spoon on remaining bananas and whipped cream.
Drizzle with chocolate sauce and walnuts.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: vegetable-burger soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Stir in 2 cups water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Using large skillet, cook eggplant, tomato, pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Combine chili sauce and water.
Add to the cooked vegetables.
Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and chill. Good with cauliflower, celery, carrot sticks, potato chips or crackers.

title: southwest taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°.
Partially bake pie crust for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°. In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.

title: elderberry wine
directions: Place 1 gallon berries in crock.
Pour warm water over berries. Let stand without stirring for 10 days.
Then strain off carefully through sieve.
Do not crush berries.
Add sugar.
Bottle one month later.

title: surprise hawaiian dessert
directions: Cut up	bananas on top of crust.
Mix in bowl sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Spread this over the bananas. Pour pineapple
on	top
of this.
Spread Cool Whip over this. Garnish with coconut, cherries, pecans or walnuts.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put into a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, oil and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Spoon out on cookie sheet in small balls.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: the devil's brownies
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits on top.
Bake in slow 300° oven for 40 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: easy milk chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in cocoa until melted. Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add more milk, if necessary, to make a soft spreading consistency.
Spread on cake or brownies and let set about 1 hour until firm.

title: orange roughy on the grill
directions: Heat your grill to high heat.
Pour yourself a glass of wine. Wash the fish and pat dry with a paper towel.
Slice lemon and chop onion and pepper into bite size pieces.
Arrange fish on a layer of tinfoil and add lemon slices, peppers and onions.
Place a top layer of tin foil over the fish and seal shut.
Place on hot grill for 15 minutes.
Pour yourself another glass of wine and enjoy.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar and drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy cheese fondue
directions: In saucepan, simmer wine and garlic.
Combine cheese and flour gradually; blend into wine.
Heat until cheese melts.
Blend in soup and heat, stirring, until smooth.
Put into fondue pot. Serve with bread cubes.

title: chicken marbella
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken and next 9 ingredients.
Cover and marinate overnight refrigerated.
Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange chicken in single layer in 1 or 2 shallow pans.
Spoon marinade over; sprinkle with brown sugar and pour white wine around them.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour, basting frequently with pan juices.
When done, remove chicken, olives, prunes and capers to a serving platter.
Moisten with a few spoons of pan juice.
Sprinkle generously with cilantro.
Pass remaining juices in sauce boat. Serves 10 to 12 people.
Can be served cold, too.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° in a large, flat casserole dish for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Cover bottom of baking dish.
Spread Veg-All over chicken.
Spread sliced mushrooms over Veg-All.
Mix soups together with 1/2 cup of broth that chicken is cooked in.
Stir until soup is one color.
Spread over chicken-Veg-All mixture.
Top with rolled crescent rolls or separated biscuits to make crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until bubbly and brown.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients except dressing; mix well.
Pour dressing over mixture and cover.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips or use as salad entree.

title: rudy's famous "omelets"
directions: Put flour in large mixing bowl; stir in salt and sugar. Add 2 cups
milk;
stir well.
Add the eggs;
blend well.
Add 1 more cup
of milk and stir vigorously.
Preheat large frying pan containing	generous amount of oil.
Pour in enough batter to cover bottom of pan.
Allow to brown over medium heat; turn over and brown
other
side.
Add
oil
as needed.
Serve with sugar sprinkled on
top then rolled up; or with fruit toppings and whipped cream.
Makes approximately 8 omelets.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix together milk and lemon juice.
Put a layer of bananas. Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans and coconut.

title: wine drops
directions: Stir together lightly sugar, shortening, egg, molasses, boiling water, soda dissolved in the boiling water, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add raisins, nuts and flour.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't ask me!
I don't know either!

title: turkey 'n stuffing pie(ready to bake in just 12 easy minutes.)
directions: *Three cups leftover stuffing may be substituted for butter, water and stuffing crumbs.
If stuffing is dry, stir in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until moist but not wet.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Scald evaporated milk and water in top of double boiler. Blend brown sugar, flour and salt; add egg yolks and water.
Stir into hot milk and cook over boiling water for 10 minutes, stirring until thick and smooth.
Cool and add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell or crumb crust.
Cover with meringue made by gradually beating sugar into stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in slow oven (325°) about 20 minutes.

title: carolyn's yummy vegetables
directions: Put all in a bowl and pour boiling water over to thaw.
Drain and put into buttered casserole.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 small jar Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and salt well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring; beat well.
Add flour and milk; end with flour.
Coat cherries with part of flour.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° (cold oven) for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Do not open oven.
Remove cake immediately.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in a little salted water or broth until tender.
Add tomato juice, seafood sauce and garlic powder.
Add green beans, gravy (can use a gravy mix) and chicken.
Stir in flour.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coffee ice cream
directions: Dissolve coffee in evaporated milk.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add evaporated milk, whipping cream, vanilla and salt.
Chill in freezer container before freezing in ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: mom's yellow cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, water, oil and eggs together.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Bring confectioners sugar, orange juice, water and butter to a boil.
Pour over cake while it is still hot.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten egg.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Mix.
Add dates and pecans.
Roll into 6 rolls; wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Cut about 1/4 inch thick. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: baby food carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together, fold in alternately with carrots.
Bake in 3 layers at 300° about 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Partly cook sausage and drain.	Place in 2 quart baking dish. Cover
with
layers
of rice, potatoes, onions and carrots.
Add tomatoes
with
juice and sprinkle salt and pepper over top. Cover baking
dish	and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sack packer cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Shape into small balls. Roll in coconut.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Unfold pie crust; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Remove crust; cover with chips and bake 1 minute or until chips are soft.
Spread chips to cover crust.
Top with pie filling.
Cool.

title: buenos burritos
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain.
Stir in picante sauce, cumin and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes or until most liquid has evaporated.
For each burritos, spoon a heaping 1/4 cup meat mixture down center of tortilla, top with 3 tablespoons of cheese. Fold tortilla over one end of the filling and roll.
Serve with lettuce, sour cream and additional picante sauce, as desired.

title: popsicles
directions: Fill ice cube tray with soda, juice or Kool-Aid.
Cover with foil.
Poke stick in each cube.
Put in freezer until frozen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup cheese.
Grease pan well.
Pour half mixture in pan.
Sprinkle cup of grated cheese over mixture.
Add remaining mixture and bake at 450° until done.

title: roast loin of pork
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
With the point of a sharp knife, make several cuts across the top of the roast, about 1 1/2 inches in depth, toward the center of the roast.
Insert garlic slivers and parsley into each cut.
Season the outside of the roast with the remaining ingredients.

title: tomato jam
directions: Scald, peel and chop tomatoes.
Place in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Measure 3 cups of tomatoes.
Place in a large saucepan.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice and sugar.
Mix well.
Place over high heat.
Bring to a full, rolling boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add pectin immediately.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
Stir for 5 minutes to cool.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Cover at once with 1/8-inch melted paraffin.
Yields 4 pints.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375 degrees for an hour or until done.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and beat well, then add the grated chocolate, chocolate chips and the nuts and stir until smooth. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
The chocolate chips will come to the top while baking and will form icing.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, Wesson oil, red food coloring, vanilla and vinegar together.
Mix salt, baking soda, cocoa in flour, then add to mixture.
Add buttermilk.
Pour into greased cake pans (3). Bake on 350° about 20 minutes or until done.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Layer apple slices in pie shell.
Mix together apple juice, cinnamon, nutmeg and cornstarch in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour over apples and place 2nd crust on top.
Butter lightly and bake at 350° for 60 minutes, until golden brown.

title: graham cracker pie crust(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into an 8 or 9-inch pie pan. Chill before adding filling.
Total calories per crust:
352. With sugar:
384 calories.

title: rave review cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients (cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil).
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: *Optional:
May use raisins instead of chips.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Sift into a bowl the flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, oil and vanilla until smooth. Spread in ungreased 9-inch square baking pan.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix the flour, shortening, sugar and salt well.
Now mix the egg, water and vinegar.
Combine the two mixtures, a little at a time, until all the dry ingredients are moist.
Mold together with hands. Chill before rolling or keep in refrigerator up to a week. Makes 2 double crust 9-inch pies.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken for 40 to 45 minutes, until done.
Cool.
Remove meat from bone.
Heat both cans of soup with the 3/4 cup of milk on medium heat until warm.

title: crunchy oven-fried flounder
directions: Move oven rack to position slightly above the middle of oven. Heat oven to 500°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
If fish fillets are large, cut into 4 serving pieces; pat dry.
Mix sour cream, lemon juice and chili powder.
Dip fish into sour cream mixture; coat with chips.
Place in baking dish. Drizzle butter/margarine over fish.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Makes 4 servings (195 calories/serving).
Protein 18, Carbohydrate 4, Fat 12, Cholesterol 60, Sodium 190.

title: chocolate-nut chess pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl; mix well. Combine eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir into sugar mixture, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until set.
Cool.
Sift powdered sugar over pie, if desired.

title: spam dip
directions: Cream together until smooth the top 5 ingredients.
Dice Spam as small as you can.
Add Spam to rest of mixture.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: no cook the noodles lasagna
directions: Add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce to hamburger.
Coat bottom of pan with sauce.
Layer the following in a 9 x 13-inch pan: noodles (do not cook), sauce and cottage cheese and top with both cheeses.
Repeat layers so there are 3 layers.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and refrigerate.
Reheat the next night.
This is best when reheated.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 dozen.

title: golden punch
directions: Add water to frozen orange juice and lemonade as directed on can. Mix all ingredients together and serve chilled.
