title: layered fruit 'n' cheese dessert squares(makes 15 servings)
directions: For crust, in a small bowl, combine cracker crumbs, pecans or walnuts, flour and the 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir in the melted margarine or butter.
Toss to mix well.
Press mixture onto the bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses and onion together.
Form into a ball or log. Sprinkle with walnuts. Chill before serving.
Add small can of diced jalapeno peppers for a little zip, if desired.
May be frozen for later use.

title: lattice-top chicken bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, peas, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spread mixture into a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: pink party punch
directions: Pour contents into a gallon jar.
Finish filling gallon jar with water.
Stir to blend.
Chill.
Serves 32 cups.

title: millie's special
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
In large baking dish or bowl, combine all the ingredients, except chow mein noodles.
Stir and mix well.
Bake for 30 minutes; add chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer and serve.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring butter or margarine, brown sugar and Karo syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour syrup over popcorn and peanuts.
Mix well.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: white christmas chili
directions: Place chicken, 5 cups water, and half of onion in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat, and cook 1 hour or until chicken is very tender.
Remove chicken, reserving cooking broth in Dutch oven. Cut chicken into bite-size pieces; set aside.

title: cocoa drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar,
Nucoa
and egg thoroughly.	Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift
dry ingredients together and stir in. Chill for at least
1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop rounded teaspoon of dough
about
2-inches
apart
on
greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8	to
10	minutes
until set.
Frost cooled cookies with cream chocolate icing.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in butter.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix heavy cream with garlic and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about an hour; baste with sauce.
Cook and drain peas; add to chicken and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar, then add whipped cream.
Spread in a pie shell and top with cherry pie filling.

title: orange-ginger muffins
directions: Combine in large bowl, making a well in the center, the first five ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into well.
Mix all until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins, 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: First peel and boil the potatoes.
Then drain off the water. Mix the pinch of pepper, 1/4 stick of butter and 1/4 cup milk into bowl.
Mix potatoes until mashed and fluffy.

title: hillbilly beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in crock-pot on high for 3 to 4 hours or in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter.
Add soup, cheese, lemon juice and broccoli.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve as hot dip in a chafing dish.
Also may be poured over 2 or 3 cups instant uncooked rice and bake as a casserole.

title: flonnie's dressing
directions: Boil fryer in water to cover until tender-done.
Remove chicken and set broth aside to cool.
Debone chicken and chop.
Saute onion and celery in a small amount of butter or cook in some of the chicken broth.
Put cornbread, loaf bread, onion, celery, seasonings, eggs and chicken in large bowl.
Pour broth over ingredients.
Do not stir until dressing is cool.
After it is cooled, blend together and pour into a Pyrex dish.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Use giblets and remaining broth for gravy.

title: tess flynn's ice cream cake
directions: Preheat oven as directed on cake mix.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
When the beef is cooked, add tomatoes and cabbage.
Cook until the cabbage is limp. Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/2 of the cabbage mixture into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour in remaining cabbage mixture.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and combine all other ingredients. Chill overnight. Salad is better after 2 or 3 days. Keep refrigerated.

title: pork chops in wine sauce
directions: Brown the pork chops over medium heat until tender.
Remove from the pan and pour off any extra fat.
Add the wine and sour cream to the pan, then add salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, basting frequently.

title: posole
directions: Boil meat (can add pigs feet) until tender.
Boil posole hominy separately until it bursts.
Do not over cook.
After cooked, mix meat with posole hominy and oregano.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Do not boil.
Extra delicious when served with red chile sauce, 1 Tbsp. sliced onions, 1 Tbsp. cabbage and 1 tsp. lime juice. Add salt if desired.

title: kahlua pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and flour. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir in Kahlua, corn syrup, evaporated milk and pecans.
Mix well and pour into crust.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until firm, about 40 minutes.
Refrigerate. Serve with whipped cream.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.
Sprinkle 1 cup buttered, toasted bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grace's prune cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, milk and oil.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to the egg mixture.
Add prunes and nuts last.
Grease and flour a flat pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is very simple to make and very good; stays moist for days.

title: orange sherbet ice cream
directions: Stir and put into ice cream churn. Churn until frozen.
Churn with rock salt and ice.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar and vanilla gradually while beating.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in pineapple. Bake in greased 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour.

title: crab salad dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Serve with wafers or crackers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake pie crust, cool and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn mixture into the prepared pie crust and garnish with chocolate.
Freeze for one hour or refrigerate until firm.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Toss lettuce and onions together.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Layer the first 9 ingredients in roasting pan in order listed. Mix soup, wine and flour with a whisk until smooth.
Pour mixture over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake stew at 275° for about 4 hours.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix together like pie crust, then add 1 beaten egg to moisten. Sprinkle mixture on top of 4 to 6 peeled and sliced apples in a buttered pan.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
May turn upside down.

title: thin lemon wafers (cookies)
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add flour, mixing well.
Stir in lemon extract; drop batter by level teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: fettuccine with broccoli and mushrooms
directions: Wash broccoli and trim into small flowerets. Peel and chop stems coarsely.
Cook broccoli in large pot of boiling, salted water (about 3 minutes).
Drain and set aside.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until blended well. Chill.

title: hot dog or spaghetti sauce
directions: Put oil, beef and onions in deep frying pan.
Fry until brown. Drain and then add catsup, water, salt and chili powder; simmer about 1/2 to 1 hour.
Can be used for hot dog or spaghetti sauce.

title: toasted coconut cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine Eagle Brand, egg yolks, water and pudding mix.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Beat in sour cream.
Stir in 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with remaining 1/4 cup coconut. Refrigerate leftovers.
Prep time:
40 minutes.
Total time:
3 hours.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool, then take fork, making a hole in both layers.
Dissolve 1 box Jell-O with 1 cup water.
Spoon on 1 layer of the cake.
Repeat with second Jell-O.
Then top with Cool Whip.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Parboil cabbage until tender.
Separate leaves.
Mix hamburger, rice, salt, onion, pepper and 1 can of soup.
Fill each leaf with mixture.
Wrap and secure with a toothpick.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Put the slices of bananas in a separate bowl then drain the pineapple juice into the bowl with bananas.
In large serving bowl, add pineapple, mandarin oranges (drained), frozen strawberries and peach pie filling.
Drain pineapple juice from the bananas and add to bowl.
Stir all ingredients together. Refrigerate all day or overnight.
Any variety of fruits can be used.
Change the pie filling to a different flavor.

title: phoebe's three day coconut cake
directions: 1st Day:
Mix together coconut, sugar and sour cream.
Let stand until next day.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix with rotary mixer until smooth.
Cut top off rye bread. Hollow out insides.
Pour in dip.
Serve with fresh vegetables and bread cubes.

title: punch
directions: At least 1 day ahead, make an ice block by freezing sliced oranges and maraschino cherries in an 8 ounce plastic container. Mix the pineapple juice, frozen lime concentrate and frozen lemonade concentrate in a drink container and refrigerate.

title: treet broil
directions: Mix together and place on hamburger buns.
Place under broiler for 5 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Peel potatoes; cube.
Add all other ingredients except tomato juice.
Cover with water and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Add tomato juice and simmer another 15 minutes.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind or put in blender the peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Put in kettle with remaining ingredients and cook 1/2 hour.
Can.

title: best-ever hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; bring to boil.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Makes about 2 cups of delicious hot fudge sauce for ice cream, etc.

title: chow mein
directions: Fry meat until brown.
Stir in bouillon, celery, onion, soy sauce and monosodium glutamate.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Shake reserved liquid and cornstarch in covered container.
Stir gradually into meat.
When thick, add vegetables and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice and chow mein noodles.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine tomato sauce, chilies, salt, oregano and cumin in small saucepan.
Cover, simmer 10 minutes. Combine cheese and onion in small bowl.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Dip tortilla in hot oil to soften; drain.
Place in baking dish.
Top with 2 tablespoons sauce and scant 1/4 cheese mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with tortilla. Pour remaining sauce over stack.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese mixture.
Continue baking until cheese is melted. Cut in wedges.

title: crab and artichoke casserole
directions: Melt butter, remove from heat, stir in flour, salt, pepper, paprika and onion.
Stir in milk and bring to a boil.
Simmer gently 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni shells and artichoke hearts as directed on packages.
Drain both well.
Combine crab, shells, hearts, sauce and sherry.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt
together
butter
and 1 cup peanut butter.
While still warm, mix with confectioners sugar.
Spread in buttered 9
x 13-inch
pan.
Melt together chocolate bits with 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Spread thinly over the first mixture.
Refrigerate and cut.

title: mixer rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water in a bowl.
Let set 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir. Add half the flour, sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes until the batter is smooth and shiny.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Wrap 1 teaspoon cheese mixture around olive.
Freeze in single layers separated with wax paper.
Bake at 400° on ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar and soda in a deep 3-quart saucepan.
Mix well with a wooden spoon.
Then add cream.
Stir carefully to keep sugar crystals in lower part of pan.
All crystals should be dissolved when candy boils.
This helps make it smooth and creamy. `Bring
to boil on medium heat, stirring occasionally, to prevent scorching.
Cook candy until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove pan from heat.
Add butter immediately.
Measure accurately.
Too much will prevent them from firming.
Add pecans and beat until mixture is thick enough to drop from a spoon.
Drop candy on wax paper or foil.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine pimento, green pepper, onion, soup, broth, salt, pepper and 1/2 of cheese.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer spaghetti, chicken and mixture.
Layer ingredients again, ending with mixture. Top with other cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: In large kettle, cook celery and onion in butter until tender; add water, chicken, carrots, bouillon, marjoram, pepper and bay leaf. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf; add noodles and parsley. Cook 10 minutes longer. Serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli. Melt cheese and 1/2 of the margarine. Mix with broccoli.
Place in greased baking dish.
Melt remaining margarine and mix with crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of the broccoli. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: grape-nut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually and fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 450° oven until light brown.

title: enchiladas el paso
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onions; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, water and seasoning.
Simmer minutes.
Place round tablespoon of each meat sauce and cheese on each tortilla. Roll up tightly.
Place seam side down in 12 x 8-inch baking dish; top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Heat soup and milk together.
Add all remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 9 x 13 baking dish with cooking spray.

title: ginger sauce
directions: Blend.
Store in refrigerator up to one week.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: swiss steak
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Flour meat.
Put oil in Dutch oven, heat, then add meat to brown. Arrange onion slices between layers of meat.
Add water and Worcestershire sauce; cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: tomato florentine soup
directions: In a saucepan, saut the green pepper, onion and garlic in oil until tender. Add tomatoes, water, basil, bouillon, pepper and sugar; bring to a boil. Stir in noodles; reduce heat. Simmer for 10 minutes; add spinach. Cook until noodles are tender. Yield: 5 servings.

title: water chestnut appetizers
directions: Wrap water chestnuts with bacon strips.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Bake 60 minutes at 300°.
Combine remaining ingredients to make sauce.
Drain off bacon grease and cover appetizers with sauce.
Bake another 30 minutes.

title: louisiana old fashioned pecan pralines candy
directions: Combine sugar, cream and water in saucepan; cook to soft boil stage.
Remove from heat; beat until creamy.
Add nuts and drop by spoonful onto buttered sheet.

title: parmesan rounds
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese, chopped onions and mayonnaise; spread on cocktail rye slices.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread the rolls on cookie sheet and bake as directed on package.
Mix together the mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Spread on crust.
Shred (processor work great) the cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, green peppers, radishes, cukes (not good in processor) and onions. Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Cut and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes in a 9-inch pie shell.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Mix in soup, milk and vegetables with the ground beef.
Put Tater Tots in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour beef mixture on top.
Top
with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach-butterscotch pie
directions: Place peaches in 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Combine sugar, flour, salt and peach syrup.
Add butter and cook until thick. Remove from heat and add lemon juice; pour over peaches.
Make lattice top crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into pie crusts. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: coffee cake(without eggs)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Take out 1/2 cup crumbs for top (optional).
Soda is added to milk.
Add milk to dry ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square pan and sprinkle crumbs over top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Put ground beef in pot, which has a lid.
Add hot water.
Work mixture with the hands until it is blended.
Add catsup as needed and plenty of chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until thick.
The grease comes to top and is easily skimmed off and discarded.

title: spicy shrimp salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water in top of double boiler.
Stir in mayonnaise. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into oiled fish mold and chill until firm.

title: overnight bubble coffeecake
directions: Place
frozen
rolls
in greased tube pan.
Mix pudding mix, brown
and	white
sugars, cinnamon and pecans together. Sprinkle over
frozen
rolls.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over top. Cover pan and leave at room temperature overnight.

title: chinese hamburgers
directions: Saut hamburger, onions and celery.
Add water chestnuts, dry rice, soups and water.
Blend together well.
Bake in casserole dish 1 hour at 350°.
Place dry Chinese noodles over top just before removing from oven.

title: taco mix dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo, taco seasoning mix, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Let chill.
Then layer bean dip, taco mix,
onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.

title: connie's texas sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, soda and flour in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Melt water, cocoa and oleo.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add sour milk, vanilla and eggs.
Bake in a large cookie sheet (greased) at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti or pasta alla putanesca
directions: Combine all ingredients in
a
bowl;
pour olive oil to cover. Let stand stand several hours; turn often.
When ready to serve warm slightly.
Do not cook or bring to a boil.
Cook pasta to package directions, drain and toss with sauce.

title: sandwich buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Add yeast mixture to all other ingredients and make softer than bread dough.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down. For best results, let rise second time until doubled in bulk. Grease hand with oleo.
Take small pieces of dough and shape into balls.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten down with hand.
Let rise for 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: irish soda bread(courtesy of the head chef at holiday inn)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Gradually add 1 cup buttermilk.
Mixture will be on sticky side.
Knead on floured board and shape into a ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Check last 10 minutes and brush top with butter.

title: brandied fruit starter
directions: Apricot or peach brandy may be substituted for plain brandy. Pears can also be used as fruit.

title: honey chicken
directions: Combine butter, honey, mustard and lemon juice; mix well.
Cut slits in chicken and lightly sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place chicken, meaty side down, in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and turn chicken; bake 30 minutes or until well done.
Baste occasionally.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Break up Hershey bars; set aside.
Spread chopped nutmeats on sheet of foil.
Cook sugar, oleo, water and white Karo to hard crack stage (300°).
Pour hot mixture over nutmeats.
Spread to cover nuts.
Place Hershey bits on top, spreading as it melts. Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Butter
large casserole dish.
Peel and slice potatoes; layer in dish.
Add layer of onion and cheese.
Make 2 layers. Place pork
chops on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; pour water in about 1/4-inch to cover bottom of dish well.
Bake at 350° to 375° for
minutes
to
hour
or until meat and potatoes are tender.

title: baked limas
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Boil in salted water until tender; drain.
Add brown sugar, bacon (cut into small pieces) and onion.
Add 1/2 cup water and prepared mustard.
Mix and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake approximately 2 hours at 350° until brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Stud oranges with cloves.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Combine with remaining ingredients in a large pot and simmer on low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 20 (5 ounce) drinks.

title: refreshing fruit and dip
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Serve dip in small bowl surrounded by sliced fruit.

title: irresistible brownies
directions: Mix flour and cocoa; set aside.
Mix sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Gradually blend in flour mix.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Makes 16.

title: old-fashioned cabbage salad
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients to boiling.
Remove from heat and let cool while chopping the vegetables.
Grate or chop cabbage, removing the heart (may use food processor).
Add peppers and onion.
Pour sugar over top along with vinegar mixture.
This can still be warm.
Salad keeps a couple of weeks in refrigerator.

title: small meat pies
directions: Line small muffin tins with crescent rolls, approximately 24.

title: bacon salad dressing
directions: Brown bacon and onion in skillet. Take from heat and drain off grease and crumble bacon. In saucepan heat sugar, vinegar and water until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat. In large bowl mix all ingredients together while warm. Keep refrigerated in a sealed jar. Serve on a lettuce salad or with watercress.

title: white fudge
directions: Take milk, sugar, vinegar and Karo and boil for 4 minutes. Stir in peanut butter, marshmallow and 2 squares chocolate if desired.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil water and oleo; add flour and salt.
Beat over heat until mixture forms a ball in the pan.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet; leave them room to expand.
Bake at 400°
for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut off the top and fill with ice cream.
Replace top and serve with strawberries or sauce.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash and cook pinto beans until done in heavy saucepan or cooker.
Keep plenty of water in while cooking.

title: souper skillet pasta
directions: In large skillet, brown and drain ground beef.
Add soup mix, oregano, garlic salt, tomatoes and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Cover.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until macaroni is tender.
Stir in Parmesan and top with Mozzarella.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Combine the next 4 ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Add the last 2 ingredients.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet for 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot steak(chinese pork steak)
directions: Brown meat.
Remove fat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high for 4 hours.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla well with electric mixer. Stir in dry sifted ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 8 cup Bundt pan Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt sweet chocolate and spread on while still warm.
Sprinkle ground nuts on top and cut into squares.

title: stir-fried turkey(microwave)
directions: Cut the turkey fillet into strips and put into a bowl.
Add the oil, soy sauce and sherry; stir.
Leave to marinate about 30 minutes.
Preheat browning dish to maximum according to manufacturer.
Stir in turkey strips.
Then add the marinade and ginger and stir quickly to seal the meal . Add the pepper and onions and microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir in bean sprouts and microwave on High for further 2 minutes.
Serve at once over rice and soy sauce.

title: pecan custard pie
directions: Prepare egg custard mix as directed on package for pie, reducing milk to 2 1/2 cups.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set, at least 3 hours.
Meanwhile, combine the sugars, pecan pieces, butter and light corn syrup in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Add the water. Continue boiling 1 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Cool, spoon sauce over individual servings of pie.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix and pour into loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with cold water and ice cubes.
Set aside about 3 hours.
Do not use metal container.
Mix all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour cold water off cucumbers.
Pack in jars.
Cover with hot liquid.
Process 10 minutes.

title: turkey chowder
directions: Cook onions in 3 tablespoons butter in large saucepan until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add turkey broth, vegetables and seasonings.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Melt remaining butter in skillet.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir white sauce into turkey-vegetable mixture and heat thoroughly.
Serve immediately. Makes 1 1/2 quarts of chowder or 4 to 6 servings.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Spray a large skillet with a non-stick coating.
Stir-fry beef strips until browned.
Add all but the last 3 ingredients and simmer, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix cornstarch with soy sauce and water.
Stir into hot mixture and continue cooking until thickened.
Serve over noodles or quick cooking brown rice.
Makes 5 servings.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat well.
Combine cornmeal and baking powder.
Stir into corn mixture.
Pour into greased 10-inch iron skillet and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: peaches and squash(an attractive side dish to serve with poultry, pork or fish)
directions: Put onion and reserved peach juice in a large skillet; bring to boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer about 2 minutes until onion is tender.

title: lemon mousse(serves 10)
directions: Stir together 3/4 cup sugar and cornstarch in 3-quart saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and food coloring.

title: cucumber delight
directions: Combine chicken, egg, mayonnaise, onion and green pepper. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Spread 1 teaspoonful on each cucumber slice.
Top with toasted pecan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Prepare dressing mix with mayonnaise and buttermilk.
Steam frozen broccoli until done (about 4 to 5 minutes in microwave). Combine bacon, mushrooms, cheese, croutons and onion.
Coat with prepared Hidden Valley Ranch dressing to taste.
Double recipe for a large group.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend 2 tablespoons melted butter and 2 1/2 tablespoons flour.
Add to mixture.
Mix well and remove from heat.
You may sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and brown in oven.
Serves 6.

title: double chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt Baker's chocolate and margarine in double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Stir sugar and vanilla into chocolate mixture.
Place in a medium bowl.
Cool.
Beat until blended. Beat the eggs in, one at a time, mixing very well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and stir into chocolate mixture. Fold in chocolate chips.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: west virginia biscuits
directions: Combine water, sugar, yeast and shortening.
Mix well.
Mix in enough of the flour to make a workable dough to roll out for biscuits.
Roll dough and cut out biscuits.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let stand 1 hour in warm place.

title: jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in large skillet and lightly brown the Rice-A-Roni.
Stir in the water and chicken flavor, then remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: monkey balls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag. Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and shake in bag. Layer in Bundt pan. Put cherries and pecans in between layers. In saucepan, melt margarine and brown sugar. Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Let set for 2 minutes. Invert on plate.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in skillet; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce and catsup and heat.
Place alternate layer of the beef mixture and cheese slices in 1 1/2-quart casserole; arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: easy fish chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onions, celery and carrots in butter for 5 minutes.
Add fish, cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently until fish flakes.
Add soup, milk and half and half. Simmer 20 minutes on medium-low heat after fish is cooked.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in greased dish for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake cake and cool. Cut into small squares and place in bottom of glass or see through bowl. Mix pudding, pie filling and pineapple. Layer on top of cake. Top with Cool Whip and garnish with fresh fruit.

title: cabbage, carrot and raisin salad
directions: Lightly toss carrot, cabbage, raisins, salt, lemon juice and sugar until well combined.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Just before serving, toss with dressing.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour in pie crusts.
Chill for several hours.
Serve cold.
Makes 2 pies.

title: football chicken
directions: Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine all ingredients, except chicken and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Pour ingredients into baking dish and place chicken on top.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle extra Italian seasoning on top of Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brown beef stew
directions: Melt shortening in bottom of stew pot. Roll meat in mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Brown meat on all sides in hot shortening.

title: coconut pecan frosting(for german chocolate cake)
directions: Combine in saucepan sugar, evaporated milk, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat until well blended with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top with desired frosting.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Slice the onion and pepper into 1/8-inch strips.
In a nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and pepper slices and saute, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until onion is slightly brown.

title: top of stove casserole
directions: In a tightly closed roasting bag big enough for your roast, marinate in Allegro overnight, turning bag before bedtime.
Put in cold oven and heat oven to 500° to 550° for 8 minutes.
Turn the oven off, but do not open oven door or the bag for one hour.

title: shrimp neptune
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In a skillet, saute shrimp in margarine for 5 minutes or until pink. Combine mushroom soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard, chives and sherry.
Mix until well blended.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, make layers, beginning with noodles, then shrimp and crab. Next, layer sauce mixture.
Spread over seafood.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix together ground chuck, spaghetti sauce and water.
Mix noodles into spaghetti sauce mix.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) baking dishes.
Top with cheese, then cover with pepperoni.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 20 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli according to package; drain.
Add all ingredients together and heat until bubbly.
Serve with large size corn chips.

title: pecan roll
directions: Crush wafer. Add milk. Mix well. Add cherries and pecans. Mix well. Use powdered sugar to form into roll. Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate.

title: yellow velvet cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups oil, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Add the soda with the buttermilk, alternating with the 2 cups flour.
Mix well, then add the vanilla and a few drops of yellow food coloring.
Pour this into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
While the cake is cooling, combine the remaining ingredients.
Cook in a double boiler until thick. Spread on cake when the cake has cooled.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Mash out with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: prawns with wine and garlic
directions: Melt butter over medium heat; turn to low heat.
Add garlic, green onions and prawns.
Saute until prawns turn pink.
Add wine; bring to simmer.
Thicken with flour slightly.
Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: california bake
directions: Cook broccoli or cauliflower.
Stir together constantly and bring to a boil, for 1 minute, milk, oleo, salt, pepper and cornstarch.
Add paprika and Swiss cheese.

title: texas tacos
directions: Saute chopped onion in bacon drippings, add ground beef, cook until done, add chopped tomatoes, picante, salt and pepper.
Fry tortillas in hot oil, drain on paper towels, either flat or folded.
Fill with meat mixture, add chopped lettuce, tomatoes, top with cheese and serve immediately.
Onions and picante may be added, if desired.

title: hot browns
directions: Preheat broiler.
Add grated cheese to cream sauce and stir to melt.
Keep warm.
Place slices of turkey on the toast.
Cover each with 1/4 cup sauce.
Place 2 strips of bacon on each sandwich.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon Parmesan on top of each sandwich. Place sandwiches under broiler.
Broil until bubbly and speckled brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mona newbern's sawmill chicken
directions: Soak fatback in very hot water until water is completely cool. Mix flour and water together for batter.
Dip each piece into batter and fry in hot cooking oil until crisp.

title: turkey noodle bake
directions: Combine milk, cream of mushroom soup and eggs.
Add egg noodles, turkey, bread crumbs, cheese and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: schmeyer banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light and add to creamed mixture.
Mash bananas and add lemon juice. Blend with creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan in 375° oven about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 pound loaf.

title: frozen pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and pecans; fold into whipped cream.
Place scoop of ice cream in pie shell.
Pour pumpkin mixture over ice cream.
Freeze at least 2 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped cream if desired.

title: marinated grilled pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with garlic salt, pepper and meat tenderizer.
Add Worcestershire sauce and marinate.
Grill pork chops over medium coals until done.

title: dutch funnel cakes
directions: Combine milk and eggs in bowl, mix well.
Set aside.
Sift 1 1/2 cups flour, salt and baking powder together.
Pour egg mixture into flour mixture.
Blend well.
Add additional flour to make thick batter.
Fill 9-inch skillet 2/3 full of oil, heat to 375°. Pour batter into 1/2 inch funnel, drizzle batter from funnel into hot oil.
Turn to brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve hot.

title: cherry banana salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan. Cook on stove over low heat until thick.
Drain the cherries.
When sauce is cool, combine the cherries and bananas with the sauce mix in a large bowl.
Top with shredded coconut. Chill until served.

title: meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until they begin to stiffen.
Add sugar, gradually beat until stiff.
Fold in chocolate bits slowly.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven.
Turn off oven at once.
Let sit overnight.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in a small amount of oil.
Add broccoli, rice, chicken soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mostaccioli(8 servings)
directions: Prepare mostaccioli noodles according to package directions. In a heavy pan, brown ground beef and onion in oil.
When almost cooked, add chopped garlic and cook for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and wine, stirring frequently.
Add basil, salt, pepper, parsley and mushrooms.
Add cooked mostaccioli; mix well. Pour into baking dish; top with grated cheese.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover for last 10 minutes of baking.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken; mix salt, pepper and paprika with the cracker crumbs.
Dip each piece of chicken into buttermilk; then roll in crumb mixture.
Fry in hot oil until done.
Drain onto paper towel to absorb excess oil.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites to form peaks.
Add sugar and whip until stiff.
Add extract and coloring.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop small spoonfuls on a foil-covered cookie sheet.
Turn oven off.
Immediately place cookies in oven and close the door.
Leave overnight.
Do not open oven door!
Try cherry or strawberry flavor with red food coloring.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add oranges and pineapple and let set for 1 hour or until slightly thickened in refrigerator.
Mix in sour cream and chill until set.

title: steak house slaw
directions: Bring the vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed, black pepper and turmeric to a boil.
Cool; pour over cabbage, carrot and onion mixture.

title: dip for fruit plate
directions: Mix together the night before and refrigerate.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well for 1 or 2 minutes.
Spray two loaf pans with "Pam".
Pour mix into pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top will crack.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, water and pumpkin and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir just enough to mix well; add raisins and nuts.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin with balsamic-raisin sauce
directions: Place raisins and wine in heavy small saucepan and let stand for 8 hours.
Add brown sugar and 1 tablespoon vinegar to raisin mixture.
Boil over high heat until liquid is reduced to 1 tablespoon, about 7 minutes.
Add chicken stock and continue to boil until mixture is halved.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Heat olive oil in large ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat.
Add tenderloins and cook until brown on bottom, about 3 minutes.
Add onion and shallots and continue cooking until pork is brown on all sides and onion is tender, about 6 minutes.
Add garlic.
Place in oven and cook until thermometer in thickest part registers 140°, about 4 minutes.
Transfer pork to platter.
Tent with foil to keep warm.
Add raisin mixture to skillet.
Boil, scraping up any browned bits in skillet.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon vinegar. Remove from heat and whisk in butter.
Season sauce.
Keep warm.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup to a boil.
Break up cream cheese.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup. Blend in mayonnaise.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dice chicken.
Mix ingredients together.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (depending on how fast oven cooks).

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread into greased 9 X 13 baking pan.
Bake at 350 until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into 1 X 2 pieces.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Bake in 17 x 13-inch pan for 15 or 17 minutes.
In large saucepan, heat Carnation milk, sugar and marshmallows.
Heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and mix well.
Pour over cool cake.
Mix remaining sugar, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Add almonds. Pour over cooled cake and serve.

title: cheese strata
directions: Trim crust off bread.
Arrange 4 slices in squre 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover bread with slices of cheese, then top with slice of bread (sandwich like).
Beat eggs, milk and salt together.
Pour over bread.
Let stand one hour.
Bake in 325° oven about 40 mintues or until bread is puffed and lightly browned.
Serve plain or top with jelly.

title: low-fat crispy fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray cookie sheet lightly with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine buttermilk and hot pepper sauce in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Remove skin and fat from chicken; discard.
Rinse chicken under cold water; pat dry.
Place in buttermilk mixture, turning to coat.
Set aside.

title: banana apricot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add apricots.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring just until well blended.
Turn into a 9 x 5-inch glass loaf pan that has been greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on wire rack.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Blend in applesauce.
Add egg. Sift flour, salt, soda and spices.
Add to applesauce mixture. Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Chill 12 hours before serving.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Heat 1/2 cup sugar in heavy skillet, without stirring, until it melts to a golden brown syrup.
Stir as you add 2 tablespoons butter and the remaining 1 cup sugar.
Add hot water gradually; stir constantly.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir until the sugar is dissolved (about 10 minutes).
Combine flour, baking powder, 3 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Cut in the remaining 3 tablespoons butter with a pastry blender until the mixture is like coarse cornmeal.
Add nuts.
Stir in milk and vanilla; mix until moistened.
Drop the mixture in slightly rounded tablespoonfuls into gently boiling caramel sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in a dumpling comes out clean.
Do not uncover while cooking.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 dumplings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls in dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: ernest t. bass rock bars
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, cream the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in the egg.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Blend the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture and add nuts.
Spread the batter into the prepared pan and sprinkle chocolate chips on the top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 2 minutes.
Remove and score with a knife to create a marbled effect.
Return to oven and bake for 13 to 16 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add sour cream, 1 tablespoon mayonnaise, 1 teaspoon minced onion and 1 cup cucumber.
Add salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cover and place in refrigerator for several hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Add to buttermilk, then add buttermilk-yeast mixture to flour.
Mix well.
Turn out on board or pastry cloth; roll or pat to desired thickness.
Cut biscuits; dip in melted butter and place on greased pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator
for a week.

title: chocolate delight truffle
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed.
Prepare pudding mix as directed.
Thaw Cool Whip.
Smash Skor bars.
Prepare in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: ann's coffee cake
directions: In a bowl, sift together all dry ingredients.
In second bowl, cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix, one at a time. Stir dry ingredients in with creamed mixture. Spread 2/3 of the batter in greased 12 x 15-inch pan. Spread the pie filling over this.

Put the rest of the dough on by spoonfuls here and there over the top. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. While still warm, drizzle on a powdered sugar glaze made with powdered sugar and hot water.

title: berried treasure pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Spread in pie crust pan.
Put strawberries on top of spread.
Make topping mix as directed on box.

title: chicken-rice bake
directions: Cook rice in salted chicken broth until tender.
Do not drain. Place alternate layers of rice and chicken in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour Milnot over mixture.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into cakes.
Fry in oil until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients. Put in 2 quart greased baking dish. Combine bread crumbs with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Saute 5 minutes and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
Yummy.

title: strawberry lover's pie
directions: Prepare and bake the 9-inch pie shell.
Let cool on a wire rack.
In a heavy, small saucepan, melt the semi-sweet chocolate and the butter over low heat.
Spread the chocolate mixture evenly over the bottom and sides of the pie shell.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add and continue mixing.
Add oats and mix.
Press 1/2 of dough into 12 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with apricot filling. Crumble remaining dough over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
(You can use any kind of filling.)

title: italian spinach salad
directions: Marinate mushrooms in salad dressing 1 hour in refrigerator. Toss lightly with spinach and lettuce.
Top with sliced egg. Serves 6, 35 calories per serving.

title: judi's monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Combine granulated and cinnamon and roll biscuits in the mixture (toss optional raisins in).
Combine brown sugar and margarine and gently heat until melted.
Place biscuits in greased Bundt pan.
Pour brown sugar and margarine mixture over biscuits.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 25 minutes.
Best served warm but good cold.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in an 8 x 12-inch pan and top with green onion, green pepper, diced tomato, shredded lettuce and Cheddar cheese.

title: weight watcher's cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium saucepan, combine first 7 ingredients.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add beef, 3 ounces cheese and rice; stir until cheese melts.
Turn into an 8 x 8-inch pan treated with nonstick spray. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven; allow to sit 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.
Divide evenly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: delta bars
directions: Make a meringue by beating 1 egg white until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1 cup brown sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Spread meringue over dough.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Cut while warm.
Makes 24 (2-inches).

title: red beet cake
directions: Boil beets and put through strainer or blender.
Mix everything together and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Dip tomato slices in egg and then in flour and cornmeal mix. Fry until golden.

title: chili chip casserole
directions: Brown beef; add onion, seasoning, paste and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle 2 cups corn chips in dish; spoon 1/2 of mixture, 1/2 beans, 1/2 olives and 1/2 cheese layer.
Sprinkle rest of chips on top.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes; uncovered at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tangy stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut 1/2-inch thick slice from stem end of each tomato; scoop out centers and chop finely.
Sprinkle inside of tomato cups lightly with salt; turn upside down on paper towels to drain. Refrigerate.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 batter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine egg, liquid and corn. Add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until moist.
Drop batter in deep, hot fat by tablespoonfuls.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain.

title: sauteed chicken and walnut salad
directions: Saute garlic and ginger in oil in wok or fry pan.
Add chicken.
Saute until done, drain and set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Microwave chicken 6 minutes per pound.
Debone chicken and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine; add onion, water chestnuts (chopped or sliced), soups and milk.
Stir well and pour over chicken.
Mix the stuffing with broth and sprinkle by hand over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions; simmer in salt water 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Add vinegar, sugar and mustard and cook 20 minutes.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: casserole roasted chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken cavities with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Peel onions.
Scrub potatoes; pare a band around the center of each.
Melt butter or margarine with the vegetable oil in a large, heavy, flameproof casserole or Dutch oven.
Add chicken;
brown on all sides.
Combine boiling water and instant chicken broth in a 1-cup measure, stirring until dissolved.
Add to casserole with chicken.
Place the onions, potatoes and carrots around chicken.
Sprinkle with basil and remaining 1 teaspoon of salt.
Cover.
Bake in a slow oven (325°), basting once or twice with juices, 1 1/4 hours, or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken fried steak with country gravy
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and seasoned salt together.
Dredge cube steaks in mixture.
Fry in oil; set aside meat.
Stir bottom of pan; add flour and cook until golden.
Add milk and stir with whisk until gravy thickens.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 12 x 10 x 2-inch Corning Ware dish.
Pour well mixed ingredients in baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.

title: fruit spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form a ball and roll in crushed nuts or put in a bowl.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt oleo.
Add flour and chicken broth.
Add salt and pepper and boil about 1 minute.
If too thick, add some milk.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or dish with beef slices. Place piece of bacon over each chicken breast.
Mix soup and sour cream or yogurt.
Pour mixture over all.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Several hours ahead mix broccoli, onion and raisins with dressing.
Add cashews and bacon bits just before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Combine potatoes with chicken broth, water and bay leaves in saucepan.
Cook until potatoes are tender; discard bay leaves. Saute onion in oil in skillet.
Add onion and corn to potatoes in saucepan; reserve drippings in skillet.
Stir flour into drippings in skillet.
Stir into soup.
Add half and half and shrimp.
Cook over medium heat for 1 minute or until thickened to desired consistency.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix well.
Use for vegetables (carrots, celery, peppers, broccoli, cauliflower, etc.).

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter together.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
This pie freezes well.
Let come to room temperature before serving.
Recipe may be halved.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken and let cool, chop chicken up in blender real fine. Blend tomatoes, corn, and onions. Add milk to the broth. Add chicken. Cook on low heat 1 to 2 hours.

title: spiced tea cooler
directions: Combine water, cloves and cinnamon in a saucepan.
Cover and simmer over low heat 10 minutes.
Stir in honey and orange juice; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add tea bags; cover and steep 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags; cool slightly and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apricot nectarine salad
directions: Mix jello and milk.
Add pineapple with juice and pecans.
Add Cool Whip. Stir well. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours before serving. Better to chill overnight.

title: meatballs with spicy pineapple sauce
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch and ginger.
Gradually add pineapple syrup, blending until smooth.
Add orange juice and maple syrup.
Cook over medium heat about 4 minutes, until clear and thickened.
Stir in pineapple and meatballs.
Heat an additional 12 to 15 minutes or until meatballs are heated through.

title: spoonbread
directions: Take 1/3 of dough and shape into oval shape.
Place on pastry sheet and using rolling pin (filled with warm water) roll into rectangular shape, approximately 1/4-inch thick.

title: tomato vinaigrette
directions: With mixer on slow, blend oil and vinegar.
Gradually add sugar; mix until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in tomatoes; add remaining ingredients.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours prior to use.
Makes 1 quart.

title: mazette
directions: Brown meat in skillet. Add celery, onions, garlic or powder with 1 tablespoon water. Cover and steam until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat. Cook noodles according to directions. Add to beef mixture. Add tomato soup and mushrooms. Add salt and pepper to taste. Spread in 3-quart casserole or 2 (1 1/2-quart) casseroles. Top with cheese. This can be refrigerated or frozen. Bake at 350° until bubbly, 1/2 hour or so.
If frozen, put in cold oven at 250° until hot through.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add flour a little at a time, beating well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: p.e.o. bean soup
directions: Night before, wash beans thoroughly.
Place in large kettle and cover with water.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons salt.
In the morning, drain and add 2-quarts water and ham or hamhocks; simmer slowly 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer another 30 minutes.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add onions, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Stir into pot the flour mixture (stir flour and water together), tomato sauce, bay leaf, salt and pepper to taste, oregano, sweet basil, Creole seasoning, cayenne pepper and chili powder.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook until shrimp are pink.
Serve over hot rice.
(This dish is delicious, too, if you substitute crawfish for the shrimp.)

title: cheese cranberry bread
directions: Mix cranberries and 1/2 cup sugar well.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together into a large bowl.
Mix in the sugared cranberries, walnuts, orange peel and cheese.
Beat the egg, milk and butter together.
Add to mixture in bowl; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool bread 10 minutes in pan or on wire rack; remove from pan and cool before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: choose-a-fruit twists
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough; seal perforations to form 2 rectangles from each package.
Pat each into an 8 x 4-inch rectangle.
Spread cream cheese on rectangles; top with the preserves and chopped nuts.
Cut each rectangle into 4 (8 x 1-inch) strips.
(You will have 24 strips.)
Fold each strip in half crosswise and twist.
Transfer twists to a lightly greased, foil lined baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: snickers brownies
directions: In double boiler or microwave, melt caramels and 1/2 of the condensed milk. Set aside and keep warm.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: In large bowl, mix all three.
Stir around until all potatoes are coated.
Bake in cake pan (10 x 12-inch) at 450° for
40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Keep uncovered.

title: baked swedish rice pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in a large casserole or pan.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with cinnamon sugar.
Pudding may appear thin but it thickens as it cools.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onion (if used).
Drain off fat and cool.
Mix well the 2 packages of cream cheese with 1 package taco seasoning.
Take a glass serving platter and spread cream cheese mixture with a rubber spatula onto it.
Sprinkle the cooled ground beef evenly on top of this.
Sprinkle tomatoes, green bell pepper and black olives on top of this.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Sprinkle about 1/2 to 3/4 of remaining package of taco seasoning evenly on top of the shredded cheese; chill overnight.
Serve with Fritos, Doritos or tortilla chips.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil all ingredients, except for corn and soda, for 5 minutes. Mix well and stir occasionally.
Remove from heat; add soda, stirring in quickly.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Put in 2 flat pans and place in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Remove and completely cool.
Store in tightly closed container.
Peanuts may be added.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; seasoning to taste; drain.
Place in a casserole dish.
Pour beans on top of meat.
Mix tomatoes and soups in a mixing bowl; place chips on top of beans.
Pour soup mixture over chips.
Slice cheese very thin and layer on top. Bake at 350 degrees until cheese is melted.

title: cream of potato and onion soup
directions: Boil the onions and potatoes together until tender.
Drain, saving 1 cup of the water.
Rub the vegetables through a coarse strainer.
Make a white sauce of the flour, margarine, milk and potato-onion water and combine with the potatoes and onion pulp. Season with chopped parsley, salt and pepper.
Beat with egg beater and serve with toasted bread fingers.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In baking dish, layer all items until all is used.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Jif, Crisco, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg and beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly with tines of fork. Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until set and beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on sheet and then remove to foil on countertop to cool completely.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add the G.W. broth powder, eggs and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased casserole.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Pour Jell-O into hot water and stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar and salt and stir.
Add carrots and pineapple and blend. Pour into Jell-O mold and put into refrigerator until set.

title: banana pops
directions: Peel bananas and slice in half crosswise.
Brush bananas with orange juice.
Insert skewers in cut end of bananas and place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Freeze until firm.

title: caramel corn in microwave
directions: Put 4-quart popped corn in brown grocery bag.
Combine oleo, brown sugar, white syrup and salt.
Bring to rolling boil.
Boil 2 1/2 minutes after rolling boil begins.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Stir well.
Pour over corn in bag, stir to coat corn.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out and shake bag good.
Return for another 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out; shake again.
Spread out on cookie sheet to cool.
Stir to keep separated while cooling.

title: date bars
directions: Mix by hand.
Cook dates, sugar and water over medium heat until thick and smooth. Remove from heat and add, mixing by hand, vanilla, 1/4 teaspoon salt and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal, brown sugar and butter and mix until crumbly.
Spread 1/2 of oatmeal mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread date mixture over.
Crumble remaining oatmeal mix over; press to flatten.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled banana peppers
directions: Pack banana peppers in jars.
Put 1 tablespoon salt in a quart of peppers.
Heat vinegar to boiling.
Pour boiling vinegar over peppers.
Seal.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla extract.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into three 9-inch or four 8-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Place sliced bananas between layers with the frosting.

title: dip
directions: Melt together in microwave until softened.
Serve with taco chips.

title: dill dip
directions: Stir together.
Tastes better if made ahead of time to allow for flavors to blend.

title: sweet potato pon
directions: Mash potatoes.
Mix all this up and pour into a casserole dish.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies in blender to make crumbs.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Cream together milk, pudding and vanilla.
Combine together the 2 mixtures.
Fold in Cool Whip. Take 1/2 Oreo crumbs and pour into the container you are going to leave cake in.
Combine the mixture with the crumbs.
Pour the remaining crumbs on top.

title: creamy spinach bake
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Let cool; crumble and set aside.
Combine spinach, sour cream and soup mix; stir well.
Spoon into lightly greased 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with bacon.

title: snow cream
directions: Beat well and add snow to desired consistency.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in greased and floured tube pan.

title: zucchini delight
directions: Place melted butter in casserole dish.
Arrange zucchini, onions and peppers in layers.
Sprinkle bread crumbs, oil and shredded cheese over mixture.
Top with sauce.
Cover and bake for 50 to 60 minutes in 375° oven.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: stew beef over rice
directions: Place stew beef in a 2 quart pyrex dish.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over the beef.
Spoon celery and mushroom soup evenly over beef.
Cover and bake at 325 degrees for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: tunnel of fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: jello squares
directions: Will need an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch or smaller greased glass pan.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise together until smooth.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Smooth onto any kind of sliced bread. Cut into fancy shapes for party look.

title: sweet and sour meatballs(good hot or cold)
directions: Shape the ground beef into small meatballs.
Saute or broil until browned.
Mix 1/2 cup water, sugar, salt, vinegar and green pepper in a saucepan; simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine the cornstarch and 1 tablespoon cold water; add it to the hot mixture. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cool.
Add paprika.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Add the meatballs; stir to coat.
This can be refrigerated for several days.
Serve hot or cold.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breast in greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Top with slices of cheese.
Mix wine and soup together and spread over cheese. Top with crushed stuffing.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Spread the stew meat over the bottom of a roaster or Dutch oven.
Cut the carrots, celery, potatoes and onions into large pieces.
Arrange them over the meat.
Pour the canned tomatoes over all, then pour the cans of water over the tomatoes.
Sprinkle with the tapioca and seasoning.
Cover and bake at 275° for 4 hours. (There is no reason to look during this time.)
Then, remove the cover and bake 1 hour more (this thickens the stew).

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding according to package directions.
Fold in milk. Next, fold in Cool Whip.
In a large serving bowl, layer pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers.
Top with vanilla wafers or additional Cool Whip.
This is Jerry's favorite!

title: banana cookies
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Set aside. Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat 1 1/4 cups sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then bananas.
Combine dry ingredients. Beat into mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill 20 to 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonful, 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken tetrizine
directions: Measure one qt. liquid broth, add green pepper, onion, and celery.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti and salt.
Cook until tender.
Add cubed chicken, pimento, cheese, mushrooms, and worcestershire.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Bake 375° for 30 minutes.
This may be prepared the night before and refrigerated before baking.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage medium fine.
Grate carrot, dill pickle and onion.
(I do all day before.)
Mix all together.
Cover; allow to marinate.
Keep well covered in refrigerator.
Will keep for weeks.

title: bacon nibblers
directions: Trim crusts from bread and slice in half.
Spread generously with undiluted soup.
Roll half slice of bread, wrap with half slice of bacon and skewer with a toothpick.
Bake on broiler rack in 200° oven for 2 hours.
Serve immediately.

title: punch for 75
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on package.
Add Hi-C and pineapple juice.

title: lasagna(low-fat)
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces or process in food processor. Cook noodles.
Add chicken to sauce and season.
Place alternating layers in pan:
sauce, noodles, Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella.
Finish with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: jello salad
directions: Fix Jell-O according to directions on box.
Mix remainder of ingredients in Pyrex dish and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: potatoes and pork chops
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan liberally with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, milk, sugar and dash of salt until it boils and thickens.
Beat 3 egg yolks.
Mix with small amount of hot mixture, then mix all together.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add margarine or butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cover and cool in refrigerator, then fold in sour cream.
Pour into 1 baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: heavenly pies
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Toast pecans and coconut in margarine.
Cool mixture for 3 minutes.
Add to first mixture along with caramel sauce.
Makes 2 pies.
Freeze until time to serve.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; whisk in food coloring.
Stir in cornflakes until well coated.
To keep mixture from hardening, place pot in 1 inch very hot tap water in the sink!!
Working quickly, drop 1 heaping tablespoonful mixture onto wax paper.
With greased fingers, shape cornflake mixture into wreaths with holes in the middle.
Decorate with red hots.
Store in airtight containers.
Yields about 1 1/2 dozen.
Easy for kids to help!!

title: goody bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and egg.
Spread out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar, eggs and cream cheese.
Spread over first mixture and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Do not grease pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend the sugar with flour and salt.
Add egg yolks and milk. Mix well. Add other ingredients.
Cook until thick and creamy. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made with 2 egg whites, 4 tablespoons white sugar and 1/4 teaspoon of cream of tartar. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: tuna fish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Patty into 3-inch cakes.
Brown in small amount of cooking oil at medium heat on both sides.
Yields 6 to 8 cakes.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Cut cheese in small pieces.
Mix in bowl all other ingredients.
Split and butter buns.
Fill buns with mixture and replace tops.
Heat in paper bags on baking sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be made in morning, leave in refrigerator. Heat when ready to serve.

title: sunkist lemon pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks real good.
Gradually add sugar, beating to keep from curdling.
Put in cornstarch, salt, butter and hot water.
Cook until thick, stirring all the time. Grate the lemon and squeeze the juice.
Add the rind and lemon juice to the mixture.
Put into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made with the 3 egg whites and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake at 300°.

title: individual beef wellingtons
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add mushrooms and process until finely chopped.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add mushrooms, shallot and garlic, saute 2 minutes or until tender.
Stir in flour, marjoram and pepper.
Gradually add 1/4 cup consomme; stir well.
Cook 5 minutes or until liquid evaporates, stirring constantly (mixture will be thick).
Remove from heat and stir in parsley; set mixture aside.

title: marinated beet and onion salad
directions: Combine beets, beet juice, onions, vinegar and Equal in a medium bowl; cover tightly. Chill at least 8 hours before serving. Drain before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: black forest cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Mix until blended, then beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Partially cook rice (half done).
Pour off excess water. Cool.
Cut out core of cabbage.
Steam cabbage in Dutch oven to soften leaves.
Remove leaves gently; drain.
Combine cooked rice, ground beef, pork, minced onion and garlic; salt and pepper to taste.

title: german sour green beans
directions: Cook schnitzel beans until tender.
Make a mixture of butter, Crisco and onion and put in frying pan.
Saute until onions are transparent.
Mix a little water and sugar in vinegar.
Mix flour in onions and grease.
Add liquid.
This will thicken and turn white.
Put over beans.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onion in frying pan.
Add hamburger and water; let steam until hamburger is well done.
Add beans and soup and let simmer. Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Melt chocolate in heavy saucepan over low heat. Add powdered sugar and next 4 ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture is smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and let the mixture cool. Spread 1/2 cup chocolate sauce in crust.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup pecans.
Freeze 10 minutes. Remove from freezer and spread 1 cup ice cream over pecans. Freeze 20 minutes. Repeat layers twice.
Cover pie and freeze at least 8 hours. Drizzle remaining chocolate sauce over pie.
Pipe whipped cream onto pie and sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Dip chicken in beaten egg, then flour; cook in small amount of oil until browned.
Place chicken in a long baking dish.
Combine sauce ingredients in a saucepan; boil for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Chicken will absorb sauce.
Excellent party finger food or as a main dish.

title: quick 'n easy strawberry pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish or pan.
Place strawberries in melted butter.
Make batter of flour, sugar and milk and pour evenly over strawberries.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: angel salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: lazy pickled beets
directions: Heat together in a saucepan until it comes to a boil.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and walnuts. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool

title: vegetable chowder deluxe
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; heat to boiling and simmer 1/2 hour.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling and cook 5 minutes.
Add to vegetables with the cheese, pimento and paprika.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup, eggs and pecans.
Mix well. Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan in listed order.
Do not mix. Just dump it in!!
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fruity chicken rice salad
directions: Mix vinegar, honey, oil, sugar and salt in small bowl; set aside.
Bring water, carrots and raisins to boil in medium saucepan.
Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add honey dressing and toss.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 5 servings.

title: old fashion egg custard pie
directions: Heat milk
with butter until it smokes good, but do not boil. Using
a
blender
or mixer, beat eggs well.
Add sugar and vanilla;
beat
well again.
Add heated milk and mix well. You must use
a
deep dish pie crust and flute the rim as high as possible,
because	it
will
fill up to the top.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: irish bread
directions: Crumble first six ingredients like pie crust.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in well-greased cast-iron frying pan.
Make four cuts in batter.
Bake 10 minutes at 375° and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Cream white and brown sugar with butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Combine with flour, baking powder and soda.
Fold in Rice Krispies, oatmeal and coconut.
Drop ty teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir all ingredients well and chill before serving. Sets in minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Do not peel tomatoes, just slice 1/2 inch thick, and dip the slices into the corn muffin mix.
Fry in shortening until brown on both sides.
Turn only once.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and serve.

title: czechoslovakian christmas cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter until soft.
Gradually add sugar; mix until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks; blend well.
Gradually add flour; mix thoroughly.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Spoon half the batter into the prepared baking dish. Spread jam evenly over dough.
Gently cover with remaining dough. Bake for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven; cool completely.
Cut into small squares (about 12 to 16).
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Divide into balls (chill before dividing).
Roll in crushed pecans.
Wrap tightly in foil or Saran Wrap to store.
Freezes well.

title: linda's chili rellenos
directions: Wash and remove seeds from chilies.
Make layers of chilies and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan until gone.
Mix together milk, eggs and flour.
Pour over chilies and cheese mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours on medium heat, stirring with a wooden spoon occasionally.
Can or refrigerate.
Yields 5 or 6 pints.

title: chicken corn pie
directions: Cook celery and carrots in chicken broth until tender, adding corn when heated thoroughly.
Add mixture of melted butter and flour to thicken.
Add a little at a time until right consistency is achieved. Add chicken, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Place mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish. Roll out pastry dough to right size to cover top of dish.
Place on top and seal edges.
Bake at 400° until top crust is browned.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In saucepan, cook squash and chopped onions in boiling water for 5 minutes. Drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots. Fold in drained squash and onions.
