Combine melted butter with stuffing mix. Spread 1/2 of crumbs in baking dish. Add squash mixture. Top with remaining stuffing crumbs. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: pia colada cake
directions: You will need one 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add the milk, pecans, coconut and vanilla; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Refrigerate for 30 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: blt salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, milk and Ranch mix.
Mix with macaroni and all the rest of ingredients.

title: butterscotch confection
directions: Cream butter, add 2 cups flour.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: taco-bean dip
directions: Put bean dip on bottom layer.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix together.
Put on top of bean dip.
Cut up green onions, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and olives.
Put on top of sour cream mixture.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Combine gelatin and water in small saucepan, stirring well; let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat 1 minute or until gelatin dissolves, stirring constantly.
Combine gelatin mixture, strawberries and milk powder in container of an electric blender; cover and process until smooth.
Uncover and add ice cubes, one at a time, processing until blended.
Spoon mixture into 6 parfait glasses.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add hot water a little at a time. Batter will be thin.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add corn, egg, 1/2 c. cracker crumbs, onion, 2 Tbsp. butter, salt, and pepper.
Turn into 1 qt. casserole.
Combine 1/4 c. cracker crumbs and 1 Tbsp. butter. Sprinkle over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: elegant cheese chicken roll
directions: Put slice of dried beef on each breast. Roll up and secure with toothpicks. Add garlic and melted oleo.
Mix well the bread crumbs, cheeses and salt.
Dip rolled chicken in melted oleo, then roll in crumb mixture.
Put in casserole or pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: parmesan roasted potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, oil, salt and pepper in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 425°
for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: mexican salad
directions: In a large salad bowl mix lettuce, tomatoes, onions, beans and cheese.
Just before serving add chips and bottle of dressing. Toss well, serve immediately.

title: oven turkey (chicken) salad
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery.
Add cooked turkey, soup and cooked rice.
Top with pimientos, cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: glinda's baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: fruit cocktail jello salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with cream cheese until smooth.
Add fruit cocktail, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts, then fold in whipped topping.
Top with saved whipped topping and chill.

title: philly pate christmas tree
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and liver sausage, mixing well until blended.
Add onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings; mix well.
Place mixture on waxed paper.
Fold paper around sides and shape into a tree, or pack mixture into greased tree mold.
Chill.
Unmold on serving plate.
Decorate sides and base of tree with parsley.
Pipe with softened cream cheese.
Top with stars cut from pimento.

title: rice krispie chocolate treats
directions: Combine butterscotch chips and peanut butter; melt.
Add Rice Krispies until well blended.
Press half into 8 x 11-inch pan. Chill.
Mix and melt chocolate chips, sugar, butter and water. Spread over chilled mixture and put rest of Rice Krispie mixture on top.

title: chicken broccoli vegetable saute
directions: In skillet over medium heat, cook the chicken in 1/2 the margarine 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove and keep warm.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Crumble cookies into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour melted butter over cookies.
Slice ice cream and place slices over cookies side by side.
Pour caramel topping on ice cream and spread evenly. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Put in freezer for 3 hours, then eat.

title: chicken and vegetable pie(very fast, very easy...very good)
directions: While boiling water for the spaghetti, in a frying pan, add butter, oil, scallions, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add the chicken and cook for 10 more minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave on High until bubbly.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Boil water, margarine and oil in pan.
Pour over dry ingredients and beat until creamy. Add buttermilk, eggs and baking soda; beat.
Bake in floured pan for 18 minutes at 400°.

title: wassail(christmas punch)
directions: Mix all ingredients except oranges in a large pot, heating slowly.
Stuff 2 oranges with cloves.
Bake in 1 inch water in a shallow pan in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Float oranges in Wassail mixture.
Serve warm.

title: leftover coffee bars
directions: Combine raisins, coffee and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in coffee mixture and add vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well and add nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana muffins
directions: In a large bowl, blend the flour, sugar, soda, tartar and cinnamon together.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix together.
Mix in chopped peanuts or sprinkle on top. Serve with apple wedges.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together, then add applesauce, soda, spices and flour.
Then add walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 325°.
Bake in a slow oven about 1 1/2 hours or 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef and mix it with onion, beans and crumbled taco Doritos.
Let set several hours or overnight.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry meat, onions, mango and celery together until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat together.
Serve while hot.
Serve over bread or bun.

title: icebox salad
directions: Make jello as directed, except using half quantity of water. Chill. Add other ingredients.
Put in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar over low heat, stirring occasionally, until boiling.
Boil slowly to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Stir well until blended and pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch pan.

title: peach treat
directions: In a
9 x 11-inch pan or 4-quart Dutch oven (lined with foil), pour in peaches and liquid.
Sprinkle cake mix over the top evenly.
Place
butter
on top, making 3 rows of 4 each or similar.
You
can top with a few cherries or pecans.
You can also mix
the
pecans with the peaches at first.
Bake at 325° until done, about 40 minutes.

title: hardtack candy
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to hard crack stage (300°) using a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat. Add the flavoring oil. Add a few drops food coloring.
Gently stir to blend.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam or buttered. (Be sure pan has been left in cool place before this step.)

Let stand until the candy has cooled a little, then score or mark lines starting with the outer edges. Be careful not to break through the film. Continue to retrace the lines, pressing deeper each time as the candy cools.
When cold, break into pieces and dust with powdered sugar.
Store in jar.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan; let chill while mixing softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix until creamy; spread onto graham cracker crust.
Add on top, drained pineapple, then layer sliced bananas, Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Drizzle chocolate syrup and top with cherries. Chill for 4 hours.

title: patriotic parfait
directions: Will need parfait glasses.

title: polish pigs in a blanket(roll-ups)
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: krautburgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add salt and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Shred cabbage into hamburger; mix.
Add water to cover mixture.
Stir in beef bouillon.
Simmer until water is cooked all the way out.
Good on homemade buns!

title: tamales grande
directions: Put tamales in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Put chili on top of tamales.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (or until heated through).
Remove from oven and put cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with Spanish rice for a nice Mexican meal.

title: gazpacho pape'
directions: Put half of each finely diced vegetable in serving bowl. Blend remaining 1/2 chopped vegetables with tomatoes and spices in blender.
Pour mixture over vegetables and serve chilled.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Layer ingredients in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Great to serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef and onions together until browned; drain excess fat. Add all remaining ingredients and bring mixture to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are done.

title: mike's chili
directions: In large pot, saute onions in butter.
Add paprika.
When clear, add mushrooms.
Cook until tender, remove to bowl.
Brown meat; don't drain.
When browned, add onions and mushroom mix. Add beans, don't drain juice.
Add spices, catsup and water. Cook, uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove from heat.
Let set for 30 minutes and enjoy.
Better the 2nd day.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook, stirring constantly.
Pour into deep dish pie crust. Beat meringue and put on top.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Put all ingredients into 13 x 9-inch pan in the order as they are listed. Do not stir.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
You can use any fruit you desire.

title: black beans and sofrito
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic and cook until clear.
Add rest of ingredients (except beans) and cook about 5 minutes.
Mix the beans with vegetable mixture.
Spoon over hot, cooked rice.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Remove	the
green and pink from rind.	Cut into 1/2 to 1-inch strips.
Soak overnight in salt and 2 quarts of water. Boil rind in fresh water until tender.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Lay out rolls to cover a greased 11x17 inch pan.
Pinch edges together.
Bake at 400 degrees for 8 minutes.
Cool.
In large mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Spread half cream cheese mixture over cooled crust.
Add vegetables and olives to remaining cheese mix and gently stir until blended. Carefully spread over cream cheese mix on crust.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Cover with plastic wrap; chill 3-4 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle alfalfa sprouts over cheese.
Carefully cut pizza into 24 squares.
Place cherry tomato half in center of each.

title: easy italian cream cake
directions: Mix white cake mix, pudding, 1 1/3 cups water, eggs and oil on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in the coconut and pecans by hand.
Bake in a 9-inch cake pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 15 minutes; turn out on rack.

title: cranberry dip
directions: Whisk cranberry sauce with sugar, vinegar, ginger, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce, molasses and salt (if use Tabasco sauce).
Over moderate heat, stirring often, bring to boil.
Simmer until cranberry jelly is melted, about 5 minutes.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.
Serve as dip with fried chicken nuggets or wings.

title: creamy dill cukes
directions: Combine cukes, onion, vinegar and salt.
Cover and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 6 to 8 hours.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil and 3/4 cup water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. While cake is baking, mix powdered sugar, orange juice, butter and 2 tablespoons water.
Mix well.
When cake is done, take a serving fork and poke holes all over top of cake.
Pour sugar-orange juice mixture over cake before it cools.
Refrigerate before serving. May be garnished with Cool Whip.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese in chunks.
Add other ingredients.
Place in pan on low heat until all cheese is melted and well blended.

title: no wait rolls
directions: Place yeast in water; stir and set aside.
Cream margarine with sugar in large bowl.
Add egg and salt.
Add yeast/water. Add flour, two cups at a time.
Stir until well mixed.
Place in airtight container at least 6 hours or overnight.
To cook drop by tablespoons into greased muffin tins and bake until light brown. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix the jello and sugar in boiling water.
Grate apples. Grind cranberries.
Drain pineapple.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 2 cups of liquid.
Add above ingredients to jello mixture. Place in mold and refrigerate.

title: saltine cracker pie crust
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder until stiff.
Add sugar. Fold in crushed soda crackers.
Pour mixture into a buttered GLASS pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes (crust will puff up).
Let cool completely.

title: hamburg and rice
directions: Fry ground beef until brown (drain grease).
Fry celery and onion in oleo until tender.
Mix the celery and onion; ground beef; soups; rice and water together in a large baking bowl.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: spice cake
directions: Bring sugar, shortening, water and raisins to a boil.
Cool. Add remaining ingredients sifted together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with broiled Orange-Coconut Topping.
Yield: one 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, the sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can French fried onion rings. Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done. Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions on top. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: gulasch(german stew)
directions: Heat oil or cooking spray in nonstick skillet or Dutch oven. Brown meat until dark brown; add onions, garlic, salt, paprika powder and pepper.
Stir and brown until onions are golden brown. Add 3 cups of the water; bring to boil.
Add bouillon cubes, mushrooms and bell pepper.
Simmer for about 45 to 60 minutes until meat is tender.
Add wine; bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into gravy until the gravy starts to thicken. Turn off heat; add sour cream.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: honey-oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pie crust in a 9-inch pie plate. Set aside.
In medium bowl combine eggs, oats, honey, raisins, brown sugar, sunflower seeds, coconut, butter, apricots and cinnamon.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Pour stuffing into bowl.
In a skillet, heat butter and saute onion and garlic until golden.
Pour mixture with pan drippings into stuffing.
Stir until blended.
Layer tomatoes and stuffing in a shallow 2-quart casserole dish, ending with a layer of stuffing.
Sprinkle each layer of tomatoes with salt (lightly). Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown and crusty on top.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix by directions.
Make 2 layers; cool and then split.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; blend well and chill.
Reserve 1 cup of frosting.
Spread remainder between cake layers.
Combine Cool Whip and 1 cup reserved frosting; blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal airtight for 3 days.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes first and then open foil but leave potato in the foil for support.
Slice the potato lengthwise and scoop out with a spoon.
Mix with all other ingredients into a mashed texture. Refill the potato shell and leave open.
Top with extra Cheddar cheese and bake again about 10 to 15 minutes until good and hot and the cheese begins to brown slightly.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and butter in bowl.
Reserve 1/2 cup mixture.
Press remaining crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in 8 ounces whipped topping.
Spread in prepared pan.
Combine pudding mixes and milk in bowl; mix until smooth and thickened.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining whipped topping and reserved crumbs.
Chill overnight.

title: italian meatballs
directions: I have no idea how many dishes in the world include some kind of meatballs.
Probably hundreds.
There are meatballs and spaghetti, Swedish meatballs, cocktail meatballs and meatballs eaten all by themselves.
Whatever your favorite kind, they can be all made deliciously with ground turkey breast.
Just cut down on the amount of fluid normally called for in the recipe, since turkey is more moist than beef.
Here are a few recipes to get you going.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut beef chuck in half.
Put 1 stick of butter in pot; cook for 1 hour until brown.
Put 2 1/2 cups of water.
Let cook for 1 hour.
Mix 1 cup flour with hot water very good until smooth; let simmer.
Put frozen cut broccoli in same pot; let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes until broccoli is steamed.
You can put over white rice or potatoes or pasta.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt butter in oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle crumbs over butter. Mix together and press into pan.
Pour milk over crumbs. Sprinkle with coconut, then chocolate chips and nuts.
Press down firmly all over.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool well before cutting.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Add spaghetti sauce and let simmer on very low temperature approximately 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on box until soft, but not fully done.
Spray dish with Pam before placing first layer of noodles.
Layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese and repeat second layer the same.
Spoon cottage cheese by teaspoons and drop around on top of sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly throughout.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy!
Tastes better when you let it stand for a while or overnight.
Refrigerate.

title: traditional mulled cider
directions: Add all ingredients to saucepan, mixing sugar until dissolved. Bring to boiling point over low heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Ready to serve in hot mugs.
Yields approximately 2 quarts.

title: cherry salad
directions: Fold all together and freeze.
Set out 2 hours before serving.

title: bob's black-eyed pea dip
directions: Combine peas with jalapeno peppers, onion and garlic in blender.
Blend with enough pea liquid to make smooth; set aside. Combine butter and cheese in top of large double boiler.
Cook and stir over low heat until melted.
Add chiles, jalapeno liquid and pea mixture.
Heat thoroughly and serve with corn chips.
Tastes even better reheated.
Serves 12 to 14.
(Increase or decrease amount of peppers to taste.)

title: heavenly cherry angel food trifle
directions: Place cake cubes in a large bowl. Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese; beat until blended. Reserve 2 tablespoons whipped topping. Fold remaining whipped topping into cream cheese mixture. Stir cream cheese mixture and pecans into cake cubes; mix well. Spoon cake mixture into individual glasses or a crystal bowl. Spread cherry filling evenly over top.

title: classic cheese cake
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix well and blend in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in half and half and vanilla flavoring.
Pour over crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely before removing rim.
Before serving, spoon cherry preserves over the top.

title: snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 300° to 325°.
Combine ingredients except for powdered sugar in large mixing bowl by hand or mixer.
Roll in small balls and place onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 45 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: banana bread* * * * * *
directions: The next 2
recipes came from my mother, Vennie Watson's, collection.
Back during World War II, when sugar was rationed, we ate a lot of gingerbread sweetened with our own honey and molasses.

title: cheese bread sticks(good with chili or spaghetti)
directions: Cut bread into 4 slices (size of finger sandwiches).
Melt butter and pour into a bowl.
Pour cheese in another bowl.
Dip bread slices in butter and then in cheese.
Cover both sides. Place bread sticks on baking pan and cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Turn bread over halfway through cooking.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash and cut tops off about 1-inch from beet.
Cook beets with enough water to cover for approximately 1 hour.
Let cool so you can remove skins and slice.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Boil water (amount according to directions on potato box). Add salt; add potatoes, margarine and sour cream.
Cook spinach; when cool squeeze out all water.
Add to potatoes.
Add onion; mix well.
Spread in baking dish; cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: knorr dip in hawaiian bread
directions: Blend all ingredients well, except bread and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Cut out center of bread to make a nest.
Place mixture in the nest, pinch the center into bite size pieces.
Use pieces to dip.

title: curried potato soup
directions: Combine all but milk, butter and pepper.
Cover and cook until potatoes fall apart (40 to 50 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Blend in blender along with milk, butter and pepper.
Heat only until hot.
Serves 6.

title: cajun pork loin
directions: Place all ingredients, except roast, in large skillet.
Saute about 4 minutes over high heat, stirring occasionally; cool.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Chill.
Beat together softened margarine, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for about 10 minutes.
Spread this mixture over chilled crust and chill again for 15 minutes.
Layer pineapple and sliced banana on top of this.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Cut into quarters.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until frosting is of spreading consistency.
Spread over cake layers, cupcakes or brownies. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: tomato and green chile sauce
directions: Peel and finely chop the tomatoes.
Mix with California green chiles, onion, salt, and as many jalapeno chiles as pleases your taste (about 1 jalapeno to each cup of sauce will make it noticeably hot).
Makes 3 cups.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Cook
first
4	ingredients together beginning on high, then turning
to
low
heat
to	boil about 1/2 hour.
Cut or crumble bread;
add
to
mixture.
Cook a few more minutes to thicken. This can be cooked ahead and warmed before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oleo thoroughly.
Then add eggs and flour alternately until all mixed in. Mix well until the mixture doesn't feel gritty like sugar.
Add vanilla and nuts. Be sure to beat well. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chunk butter pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, stir together butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Pour mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Make Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Chill about 20 minutes or until jiggly.
Add crushed pineapple (don't drain), Mandarin oranges (drained), sliced bananas and pecans.
Mix in about 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Chill at least 3 hours, but not overnight.
If you need to make it overnight, leave out the bananas.

title: chit chat cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar and let stand 15 minutes.
Mix flour and rest of ingredients.
Make a well in center of flour mixture.
Put in eggs, oil and chocolate chips.
Do not stir yet!
Add apple mixture and stir until blended.
Stir by hand.
Grease 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 52 minutes.

title: fast main meal
directions: Cook beef in large skillet until browned, then drain off fat. Stir in chili and heat thoroughly.
Arrange cheese slices on meat mixture.
Cover and heat 1 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts. Serves 6 to 8.
Makes great open-faced sandwiches.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add dressing and mix well.
Place half in a buttered casserole and press down.
Combine soup, milk and chicken and heat.
Pour over dressing and top with second half of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash and shrimp
directions: Saute the onions and garlic in oil.
Add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are pink.
Add squash.
Cover and cook on medium heat.
Stir often.
(Don't let it stick.)
When stirring, smash squash when tender.
When almost finished cooking, add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Put bread crumbs or cracker meal on top.
Put in oven to brown.
Can also be stuffed in bell peppers.
Top with bread crumbs or cracker meal.
Place in shallow pan of water.
Brown in oven.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs which have been beaten until lemon color.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to cream mixture alternately with milk. Stir in flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.

title: apple crisp(full moon)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first five ingredients in bowl. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Layer apples and oats in buttered 8-inch square pan, pressing lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 400° until bubbly (20 to 30 minutes). Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top and brown.
Serves 4.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown skinned and chopped Italian sausage. Spoon off excess fat. Add garlic, basil, tomatoes and tomato paste. To this add 1 1/2 tsp. salt. Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes stirring occasionally. Cook noodles, drain and rinse. Beat egg, Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, 1 tsp. salt, 1/2 tsp. pepper. Layer half the noodles in 13x9x2 dish. Spread with 1/2 Ricotta filling. Add 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce. Repeat. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients well; chill.
Press in pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread over top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: jan's blue cheese dressing
directions: Blend with mixer or blender at least two full minutes.
Put into clean jar and refrigerate prior to use.
If this is too thick for you, thin with a little milk or buttermilk.
Keeps about a week or two, depending on expiration dates on yogurt and cheese.

title: orange pie
directions: Use deep dish pie crust.
Push finely ground pecans into crust.
Bake and cool.
Pour filling into crust and chill 2 hours. Top with Cool Whip.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Combine ingredients in large pan.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes and serve.
This is good to make and keep in refrigerator and heat by cups in the microwave. My children love it!

title: almond biscotti
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar well with electric mixer. Add the vanilla and almond extract.
Mix the flour, baking powder, salt and almonds and add to the first mixture.
With floured hands, shape into an 8 x 4-inch rectangle. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool and cut 1/4-inch slices, cut in two.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Cool. Cover cookie sheet with heavy-duty foil.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook hamburger; stir in salsa, water, chilies (jalapenos) and onions.
Add taco seasoning. Cook on low 3 to 4 minutes.
In 12 x 8 dish, layer 1/2 chips.
Cover with 1/2 meat and 1 cup cheese. Top with remaining chips, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sandra's grandmother's recipe(this is over 130 years old)
directions: Beat egg yolk very lightly.
Beat egg white to a peak.
Add sugar; mix all together.
Add whiskey.
Add cream.
Beat all together all ingredients.
Feed to patient as much as can take.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Steam chicken. Combine and heat chicken stock, chicken soup and seasonings. Break tortillas and cover bottom of large casserole dish. Top with broken up chicken pieces, diced chilies, cheese and onion. Layer until gone. Pour sauce over chicken mixture, making sure all is used. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hershey's kiss brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 48 mini muffin cups with foil liners.
Melt butter over medium-low heat.
Add chocolate chips; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, stirring briskly after each addition.
Gradually stir in flour until blended.
Add nuts.

title: red skelton's booze pie
directions: Crumble macaroons and add bourbon.
Mix thoroughly and press into a pie pan bottom.
Spoon softened butter pecan ice cream over macaroon mixture in pie pan, filling pan.
Smooth ice cream. Sprinkle a few macaroon crumbs on top of ice cream.
Top with whipped cream and freeze until ready to serve.

title: oriental meat pie
directions: Fry the onions until golden brown, and then remove from pan to a small dish.
Brown meat.
Add molasses, soy sauce, salt and hot water to cover.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add celery and simmer another 15 minutes.
Add chop suey vegetables and mushrooms (juice and all).
Simmer until all vegetables and meat are tender. Pour into baking dish and cover with Bisquick Meat Pie Recipe to which has been added a small amount of celery seed.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer the instant onions in water for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
This sauce is good with beef or pork.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in blender and blend for 1 minute.
Grease and flour a 9-inch pie pan.
Pour into pan and bake for 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; cool. Add other ingredients; toss and chill.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into small bites and put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soups, sour cream and onion.
Pour over chicken.
Melt oleo; mix with crushed crackers well.
Mix in poppy seed.
Top casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli and water to boil in medium saucepan, separating broccoli with fork.

title: egg in a frame
directions: Cut a hole in the bread, using a small glass.
Melt butter in frying pan on low heat.
Drop bread onto melted butter.
Break egg into the hole of the bread.
Cook until bottom of bread is golden brown.

title: cranberry sauce salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Stir until dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Stir well.
Refrigerate. May be used as a dessert, too.

title: tortilla roll appetizers
directions: Whip first four ingredients with a fork until well blended. Spread evenly on flour tortillas.
Roll up tortillas.
Wrap each roll in plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Cut into one-to-two-inch pieces just before serving.

title: tiramisu
directions: Whip eggs and sugar together until frothy.
Add Mascarpone cheese.
Whip cream with confectioners sugar.
Fold in whipped cream to cheese mixture.
Place bowl in refrigerator.

Quickly dunk ladyfingers (both sides) in Italian coffee (* a liqueur may be added to cooled coffee, if desired, Amaretto or Frangelico) and place the ladyfingers in rows, filling only the bottom of a square glass (Pyrex) dish.
Spread half of the chilled cheese mixture over the ladyfingers.
Generously dust the cheese mixture with cocoa powder.
Dip remaining ladyfingers in coffee and layer on top of cheese mixture.
Pour the rest of the cheese mixture, spreading evenly over ladyfingers.
Dust the top layer with cocoa powder and cover.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Cut into square slices and serve.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine ingredients (except soda and popped corn).
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil rapidly to hard ball stage (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat. Stir in soda quickly, but thoroughly; pour over popcorn at once in larger pan.
Stir until all kernels are coated.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 20 minutes.
Turn out onto waxed paper; allow to cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: fried oysters
directions: Roll each oyster in corn meal.
Put into pan and brown on each side.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hamburger steak with brown gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients together except onion and form into patties.
Place into frying pan with 1 tablespoon of cooking oil. Brown on both sides of patties.
Remove from pan.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with sliced onion.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; drain off fat.
Add soups to hamburger and onion.
Slice raw potatoes into casserole dish. Cover with meat mixture and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired.

title: rich pastry(great with strawberry pie)
directions: Sift together flour and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening (it will look like small peas).
Combine egg yolk and water; add to dry ingredients while tossing and stirring lightly with fork.
Add liquid to driest particles, pushing lumps to side until dough is just moist enough to hold together.
Form a ball and flatten to 1/2-inch thickness.
Roll out on floured surface to 1 1/2-inches larger than inverted pie pan.
Fit into pie pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 425° or until golden brown.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Dredge fruits and nuts with 1/2 of flour.
Cream the butter well.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Sift and measure rest of flour, adding spices.
Add dissolved soda to creamed mixture, then alternately add flour and liquid.
Pour batter over floured fruit; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: maple nut mold
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix these and cook in double boiler about half an hour, then put stiffly beaten whites of 3 eggs and a little salt in after taking off the stove. Add maple flavoring.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut Swiss or round steak into individual portions.
Add seasoned salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Brown.
Remove from frying pan and place into crock-pot or casserole.
Add mushroom soup, tomato soup, water, carrot and peas, and mushrooms. Cook in crock-pot on high for 4 hours.
In casserole, bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Whatever is leftover makes a good soup base.

title: yummy bars
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo. Mix with cake mix and 1 egg.
Mold into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Saute onion in butter; remove from stove.
Add chicken broth, half and half, salt, pepper and 1/3 cup flour; stir until smooth.
Add chicken and rice.
Pour into greased casserole and top with parsley and slivered almonds. Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup; add water to make 1 cup. Heat to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid; cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale; chill until partially set.
Blend fruits; fold into gelatin.
Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish; chill firm.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy; add eggs. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and powder with salt in bowl. Add to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9-inch pan, 35 to 40 minutes in 8-inch pan.
Cool 10 minutes and frost.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Saute onion in the oil.
Cool.
Add grated cheese, sour cream and salt.
Pour on top of cornbread mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; pack in gallon jar.
Add salt, spices and alum.
Cover with vinegar.
Cover the lid of jar with waxed paper. Let set for 6 weeks.
Take out of vinegar (throw the vinegar away).
Slice the cucumbers and to 1 pint of pickles add 1 cup of sugar.
Pack pickles back in gallon jar and seal.
Shake often and the sugar will melt and make a syrup.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add kidney beans and tomato juice.
Put seasoning in to your taste.

title: layer dip(serve with tortilla chips)
directions: Spread bean dip evenly on a rectangular serving tray. Mix salsa and sour cream; spread over bean dip. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and then with chopped green onions.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli half of recommended time and drain.
Place in bottom of large baking dish.
On top of broccoli, spread celery soup.
Slice cheese thinly; place this evenly over soup.
Cook Stove Top stuffing according to directions.
When done, place on top of cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sand cake
directions: Mix butter with sugar.
Mix in flour with baking powder and vanilla pudding.
Put eggs in one at a time and mix them.
The oven must be hot.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° heat.
Coffee cake form pan.
